n.', 4770, 0), (498128, 'No, I don''t believe in genius. I believe in freedom. I think anyone can do it. Anyone can be like Rembrandt.', 30824, 0), (498129, 'Not caring more about what other people think than what you think. That''s freedom.', 68976, 0), (498130, 'We need to see, and agree that what we seek already lives within us, and we within it. Now we know our one great task: watch for whatever promises us freedom, and then quietly, consciously refuse to see ourselves through the eyes of what we know is incomplete. Then we live wholeness itself, instead of spending our lives looking for it.', 10151, 0), (498131, 'For the rich, it''s not about getting more stuff. It''s about having the freedom to make almost any decision you want.', 34845, 0), (498132, 'The American free market system is the greatest engine for prosperity and opportunity that the world has ever seen. Freedom works.', 66992, 0), (498133, 'Implicit in true freedom of spirit lies a proud and virile will. Such glorious power of free will to choose, envisages beneficent social responsibility as manifest and welcome.', 52631, 0), (498134, 'There aren''t many people who really put their life on the line for human freedom.', 16098, 0), (498135, 'America is a fundamentally good country. We have good people with good values who want to do the right thing. But the structures of power that exist are working to their own ends to extend their capability at the expense of the freedom of all publics.', 25121, 0), (498136, 'Rock n'' roll to me is all about freedom of thought and to be whatever you want to be.', 13014, 0), (498137, 'I was a pilot and flying hang gliders, paragliders, aerobatics airplanes, and then I discovered skydiving. Free fall. Free. With nothing around you, just a parachute on your back. And you go down. But you don''t feel like you''re going down. Total freedom.', 76300, 0), (498138, 'I don''t like planning, because it robs me of freedom, so I''d like a 24 hours that was full of surprises.'