ory policies, climate-change and welfare spending, and free immigration even in wartime are gradually ruining Europe. That''s why I believe Brexit is good for British freedom, political autonomy, and the survival of democratic capitalism.', 68934, 0), (498175, 'We hold our heads high, despite the price we have paid, because freedom is priceless.', 63581, 0), (498176, 'I''m a big advocate of freedom: freedom of speech, freedom of expression, freedom of thought.', 73560, 0), (498177, 'I have tasted freedom. I will not give up that which I have tasted.', 2134, 0), (498178, 'Freedom is not of use to those who do not know how to employ it.', 140, 0), (498179, 'Novelists have always had complete freedom to pretty much tell their story any way they saw fit. And that''s what I''m trying to do.', 1484, 0), (498180, 'The whole ''bad girl'' thing allows me to mess up sometimes. And I have freedom to say more of what I want to.', 25405, 0), (498181, 'The names of Dingane and Bambata, Hintsa and Makana, Squngthi and Dalasile, Moshoeshoe and Sekhukhuni, were praised as the glory of the entire African nation. I hoped then that life might offer me the opportunity to serve my people and make my own humble contribution to their freedom struggle.', 1722, 0), (498182, 'In basic research, intellectual rigor and sentimental freedom necessarily alternate.', 76305, 0), (498183, 'There couldn''t be better parents than mine, loving yet strict. They disciplined with love. A child without discipline is, in away, a lost child. You cannot have freedom without discipline.', 69011, 0), (498184, 'I started skydiving because I loved the idea of freedom.', 8453, 0), (498185, 'The old Romans all wished to have a king over them because they had not yet tasted the sweetness of freedom.', 14801, 0), (498186, 'If they want to hang me, let them. And on the scaffold I will shout Freedom for the working class!', 65862, 0), (498187, 'The road to freedom lies not through mysteries or occult performances, but through the intelligent use of natural forces and laws.', 5203, 0), (498188, 'To talk about liberty and freedom is nice, lovely, but the important thing is to allow people to act in liberty and freedom.', 34686, 0), (498189, 'Whatever the immediate gains and losses, the dangers to our safety arising from political suppression are always greater than the dangers to the safety resulting from political freedom. Suppression is always foolish. Freedom is always wise.', 16753, 0), (498190, 'I discovered freedom for the first time in England.', 63265, 0), (498191, 'The people of the Middle East share the desire for freedom. We have an opportunity - and an obligation - to help them turn this desire into reality.', 25026, 0), (498192, 'Like a precious family heirloom, freedom is not just ours to enjoy, but to treasure, protect, and pass on to future generations.', 9148, 0), (498193, 'Freedom across the world is a result of many individuals working together.', 59452, 0), (498194, 'I love my complexion, but like so many of us, in the early years at primary school, I grew up thinking that my dark skin wasn''t a great thing. I''ve found freedom in music and songwriting, which has given me a freedom in how I present myself. I''m glad I''ve got makeup to celebrate that with.', 74133, 0), (498195, 'Laws protecting the United States flag do not cut away at the freedom of speech guaranteed in the First Amendment... Congress made this position clear upon passage of the Flag Protection Act of 1989, which prohibited desecration of the flag.', 76306, 0), (498196, 'Freedom is man''s capacity to take a hand in his own development. It is our capacity to mold ourselves.', 2467, 0), (498197, 'Private ownership of property is vital to both our freedom and our prosperity.', 73784, 0), (498198, 'I was only a working-class boy from a Nationalist ghetto. But it is repression that creates the revolutionary spirit of freedom.', 76291, 0), (498199, 'Human freedom involves our capacity to pause, to choose the one response toward which we wish to throw our weight.', 2467, 0), (498200, 'I only ask to be free. The butterflies are free.', 96, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498201, 'Liberty must be limited in order to be possessed.', 2026, 0), (498202, 'Freedom is from within.', 1836, 0), (498203, 'Freedom is never dear at any price. It is the breath of life. What would a man not pay for living?', 32, 0), (498204, 'I''m not interested in who am I. I''m interested in what''s gone, the disinheritance, what I''ve been able to become or learn or fuse with or not fuse with. A certain freedom comes... I like it that way.', 24444, 0), (498205, 'We cannot expect that all nations will adopt like systems, for conformity is the jailer of freedom and the enemy of growth.', 1680, 0), (498206, 'Routine is a declivity down which many governments slide, and routine says that freedom of the press is dangerous.', 3961, 0), (498207, 'To be frank, it sometimes seems that the American idea of freedom has more to do with my freedom to do what I want than your freedom to do what you want. I think that, in Europe, we''re probably better at understanding how to balance those competing claims, though not a lot.', 386, 0), (498208, 'The March on Washington was a March for Jobs and Freedom. There are still too many people who are unemployed or underemployed in America - they''re black, white, Latino, Native American and Asian American.', 36727, 0), (498209, 'We believe in freedom, freedom for the people of each country to follow their destiny without external interference.', 67654, 0), (498210, 'We gain freedom when we have paid the full price.', 430, 0), (498211, 'Every tyrant who has lived has believed in freedom for himself.', 4, 0), (498212, 'A person is a fool to become a writer. His only compensation is absolute freedom.', 222, 0), (498213, 'I think my first album opened a lot of doors for me to push the freedom of speech to the limit.', 392, 0), (498214, 'When I was younger, I was listening to a lot of Armenian music, you know, revolutionary music about freedom and protest. In the 70s I was listening to soul and the Bee Gees and ABBA, and funk.', 12800, 0), (498215, 'Widespread state control over art and culture has left no room for freedom of expression in the country. For more than 60 years, anyone with a dissenting opinion has been suppressed. Chinese art is merely a product: it avoids any meaningful engagement. There is no larger context. Its only purpose is to charm viewers with its ambiguity.', 20064, 0), (498216, 'Setting people to spy on one another is not the way to protect freedom.', 29501, 0), (498217, 'I want to be intentional about my freedom - in choosing it, honoring it, and protecting it. One of the best feelings I know is feeling truly free.', 12208, 0), (498218, 'Capitalism is against the things that we say we believe in - democracy, freedom of choice, fairness. It''s not about any of those things now. It''s about protecting the wealthy and legalizing greed.', 17499, 0), (498219, 'In 1960, when I came out of prison as an ex-convict, I had more freedom under parolee supervision than there''s available... in America right now.', 64134, 0), (498220, 'You have to struggle a bit, hustle a little, and be willing to go bankrupt. Once you''re willing to do that, everything opens up and you get the freedom. My joke is that next year, I''ll make the first film that costs zero dollars.', 68943, 0), (498221, 'They call them terrorists, I call them freedom fighters.', 51994, 0), (498222, 'I believe in absolute freedom of expression. Everyone has a right to offend and be offended.', 10634, 0), (498223, 'I have achieved an inner freedom.', 13541, 0), (498224, 'I am interested in anything about revolt, disorder, chaos-especially activity that seems to have no meaning. It seems to me to be the road toward freedom... Rather than starting inside, I start outside and reach the mental through the physical.', 216, 0), (498225, 'To enjoy freedom we have to control ourselves.', 113, 0), (498226, 'Many have left their families to defend our freedom. We salute their 