ld be a menace to the world and to India herself.', 32, 0), (498331, 'Freedom means the right of people to assemble, organize, and debate openly.', 66567, 0), (498332, 'Order without liberty and liberty without order are equally destructive.', 1674, 0), (498333, 'It seems that the right of freedom of speech that was enshrined in numerous constitutions is now under attack by religious institutions.', 2065, 0), (498334, 'If terrorism is to be defeated, the world of Islam must take on board the secularist-humanist principles on which the modern is based, and without which Muslim countries'' freedom will remain a distant dream.', 2065, 0), (498335, 'All theory is against freedom of the will all experience for it. ', 2087, 0), (498336, 'Freedom is a man''s natural power of doing what he pleases, so far as he is not prevented by force or law.', 1306, 0), (498337, 'I''m not afraid of terrorism at all. I''m afraid of loss of our freedom, loss of mobility, loss of global comradeship.', 1883, 0), (498338, 'For in the end, freedom is a personal and lonely battle; and one faces down fears of today so that those of tomorrow might be engaged.', 753, 0), (498339, 'Not to sound overly cheesy but I really appreciate the freedom we have in America - especially as a female.', 746, 0), (498340, 'In the Bible, God offered the Pharaoh freedom if he would just let the oppressed people free to go to the land of milk and honey. But the Pharaoh disobeyed, and he was destroyed.', 1730, 0), (498341, 'The more liberty you give away the more you will have.', 67335, 0), (498342, 'Freedom without limits is just a word.', 195, 0), (498343, 'My children came out as individuals in their own right. They were not my products. They had their own characters and were very strong-minded. I gave them a lot of freedom when they were still very young. The one thing they got from me is morals. They would never betray anyone. They are really good people.', 13967, 0), (498344, 'If social stability goes pear-shaped, you have a choice between anarchy and dictatorship. Most people will opt for more security, even if they have to give up some personal freedom.', 114, 0), (498345, 'You can''t put democracy and freedom back into a box.', 2358, 0), (498346, 'You have the freedom to live and let live, to love and let love. Granting yourself that freedom is one of the healthiest, most constructive things you can do for yourself and the people who matter to you.', 29471, 0), (498347, 'We can''t equate democracy with Christianity because the largest democracy on earth is India, which is primarily Hindu. The third largest democracy is Indonesia, which is Islamic. Democracy and freedom are not dependent on Christian beliefs.', 1229, 0), (498348, 'I don''t believe in firing professors. They have academic freedom.', 17810, 0), (498349, 'I love to deer hunt and fish and drive down the back roads in my truck. All those things basically equal freedom to me - and not having to return that message or call from my record company or management. At some point, I need to recharge.', 69334, 0), (498350, 'But it wasn''t until I graduated from Texas A & M University and joined the United States Air Force, flying C-130''s all around the globe, that I truly appreciated the blessings of freedom.', 67560, 0);
