ant to give myself the freedom not to have to be projecting my whole life ahead.', 69284, 0), (498367, 'Analysis gave me great freedom of emotions and fantastic confidence. I felt I had served my time as a puppet.', 12987, 0), (498368, 'One man''s blasphemy doesn''t override other people''s free-speech rights, their freedom to publish, freedom of thought.', 5876, 0), (498369, 'I''ve learned over the years that freedom is just the other side of discipline.', 47906, 0), (498370, 'Just as the Security Council was largely irrelevant to the great struggle of the last half of the twentieth century - freedom against Communism - so too it is largely on the sidelines in our contemporary struggles against international terrorism and the proliferation of weapons of mass destruction.', 74614, 0), (498371, 'None of us had any idea of how successful Downton was going to be. I thought I was signing up for another period drama that had a slightly modern feel. It had a freedom about it because it was coming out of the head of Julian Fellowes. Anything could happen and generally did.', 31314, 0), (498372, 'Civilization is the order and freedom is promoting cultural activity.', 1167, 0), (498373, 'People should have freedom in their pilgrimages and tours. They should come and visit historical monuments and sites - let''s say the sites around Iran - where they can easily engage in wide- scale contacts with others.', 67818, 0), (498374, 'None who have always been free can understand the terrible fascinating power of the hope of freedom to those who are not free.', 442, 0), (498375, 'The greatest blessing of our democracy is freedom. But in the last analysis, our only freedom is the freedom to discipline ourselves.', 59644, 0), (498376, 'Freedom - an occupied space which must be reoccupied every day.', 30260, 0), (498377, 'Freedom is not just declared it is exercised. ', 72448, 0), (498378, 'We do not commonly see in a tax a diminution of freedom, and yet it clearly is one.', 3690, 0), (498379, 'Freedom is the emancipation from the arbitrary rule of other men.', 69091, 0), (498380, 'It is not the simple statement of facts that ushers in freedom; it is the constant repetition of them that has this liberating effect. Tolerance is the result not of enlightenment, but of boredom.', 1464, 0), (498381, 'After the tragedy, New Yorkers are more united than ever in their vision, as well as in appreciation what living in freedom means - and that if we stand together, we can accomplish anything.', 73779, 0), (498382, 'I understand the sacrifices American servicemen and women have made to protect freedom and democracy in my country and around the world.', 67110, 0), (498383, 'I don''t labor over my drawings. I want to get freedom in the line.', 72023, 0), (498384, 'The freedom of all is essential to my freedom.', 3973, 0), (498385, 'Spirit borrows from matter the perceptions on which it feeds and restores them to matter in the form of movements which it has stamped with its own freedom.', 1769, 0), (498386, 'It''s all very well for us to sit here in the West with our high incomes and cushy lives, and say it''s immoral to violate the sovereignty of another state. But if the effect of that is to bring people in that country economic and political freedom, to raise their standard of living, to increase their life expectancy, then don''t rule it out.', 16098, 0), (498387, 'Many people don''t understand how disciplined you have to be to play jazz... And that is really the idea of democracy - freedom within the Constitution or discipline. You don''t just get out there and do anything you want.', 64810, 0), (498388, 'Jazz is about freedom within discipline. Usually a dictatorship like in Russia and Germany will prevent jazz from being played because it just seemed to represent freedom, democracy and the United States.', 64810, 0), (498389, 'So sometimes the facts are good and sometimes the facts are bad, the important thing from the point of view of a principle as broad and important as freedom of speech is that the courts articulate and set forth in a very protective way what those principles are.', 73020, 0), (498390, 'Women are not stupid, but they were not clever enough to realise that feminism did not bring freedom, but the opposite. That''s why I''m glad feminism is dead.', 1261, 0), (498391, 'From the U.S. Capitol Building to the White House, our national symbols that represent freedom to so many of us, were built by people who were anything but free.', 72947, 0), (498392, 'Freedom in a commons brings ruin to all.', 28659, 0), (498393, 'Free men are the strongest men.', 68810, 0), (498394, 'A culture without property, or in which creators can''t get paid, is anarchy, not freedom.', 16077, 0), (498395, 'Unlike other enduring characters such as ''Sherlock Holmes'' or ''Tarzan,'' being the ''Doctor'' allows you a certain freedom that is both very demanding and very thrilling. It allows you to make the character using elements of yourself.', 60251, 0), (498396, 'Freedom of the press is not an end in itself but a means to the end of achieving a free society.', 50455, 0), (498397, 'Every man must have the right fearlessly to think independently and express his opinion about what he knows, what he has personally thought about and experienced, and not merely to express with slightly different variations the opinion which has been inculcated in him.', 22669, 0), (498398, 'Bastard Freedom waves Her fustian flag in mockery over slaves.', 790, 0), (498399, 'Freedom is contagious. That''s why despots fear it so much.', 70535, 0), (498400, 'We should favor innovation and freedom over regulation.', 65800, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498401, 'Our forefathers got it; they got it, man. They took godly principles and they put them into action, and they developed our Constitution - the land of freedom where each man is accountable and responsible for his actions.', 67206, 0), (498402, 'Freedom under law is hard work. If rulers cannot be trusted with arbitrary power, it is up to citizens to raise their voices at injustice.', 68726, 0), (498403, 'There''s something contagious about demanding freedom.', 28414, 0), (498404, 'Albanians are a nation of freedom fighters who know something about living under oppression.', 73047, 0), (498405, 'Freedom is the right to one''s dignity as a man.', 8020, 0), (498406, 'Human beings crave freedom at their core.', 74018, 0), (498407, 'There are two freedoms - the false, where a man is free to do what he likes; the true, where he is free to do what he ought.', 3036, 0), (498408, 'I hear music that comes out of need, out of grief, sorrow, suffering and out of overcoming these things, as well. That journey to freedom still goes on today. It''s an incremental change, the culmination of many events in your own life and the lives of your children and grandchildren.', 76312, 0), (498409, 'Free speech carries with it some freedom to listen.', 76169, 0), (498410, 'The rewards of freedom are always sweet, but its demands are stern, for at its heart is the paradox that the greatest enemy of freedom is freedom.', 9148, 0), (498411, 'What does it mean to be an American? While each of us may have our own specific answer to that question, we likely can agree on the basic principles of America: freedom, equal opportunity, and rights accompanied by responsibilities.', 71230, 0), (498412, 'The proletariat uses the State not in the interests of freedom but in order to hold down its adversaries, and as soon as it becomes possible to speak of freedom the State as such ceases to exist.', 18097, 0), (498413, 'When you become a sannyasin, I initiate you into freedom, and into nothing else... I am destroying your ideologies, creeds, cults, dogmas, and I am not replacing them with anything else.', 72802, 0), (498414, 'The case for freedom, the case for our constitutional principles the case for our heritage has to be made anew in each generation. The work of freedom is never done.', 66788, 0), (498415, 'Freedom is never easily won, but once established, freedom lasts, spreads and chokes out tyranny.', 76313, 0), (498416, 'Some of the press who speak loudly about the freedom of the press are themselves the enemies of freedom. Countless people dare not say a thing because they know it will be picked up and made a song of by the press. That limits freedom.', 65506, 0), (498417, 'Ruby inherited the Perl philosophy of having more than one way to do the same thing. I inherited that philosophy from Larry Wall, who is my hero actually. I want to make Ruby users free. I want to give them the freedom to choose.', 73317, 0), (498418, 'The range of choice open to the individual is not the decisive factor in determining the degree of human freedom, but what can be chosen and what is chosen by the individual.', 2718, 0), (498419, 'The link between my experience as an entrepreneur and that of a politician is all in one word: freedom.', 68742, 0), (498420, 'The price of freedom is eternal vigilance. Don''t store unnecessary data, keep an eye on what''s happening, and don''t take unnecessary risks.', 41299, 0), (498421, 'And I have been able to give freedom and life which was acknowledged in the ecstasy of walking hand in hand across the most beautiful bridge of the world, the cables enclosing us and pulling us upward in such a dance as I have never walked and never can walk with another.', 9079, 0), (498422, 'Brothers in suffering, brothers in resistance, brothers in ideals and conviction. It is now our duty to further strengthen this bond in order to secure this hard-won freedom for future generations.', 76314, 0), (498423, 'A state that suppresses all freedom of speech, and which by imposing the most terrible punishments, treats each and every attempt at criticism, however morally justified, and every suggestion for improvement as plotting to high treason, is a state that breaks an unwritten law.', 76315, 0), (498424, 'I came out of the Soviet Union no longer a communist, because I believed in personal freedom.', 2996, 0), (498425, 'I didn''t come to Washington to fight against my Republican colleagues, or even against my colleagues on the other side of the aisle. I came to Washington to fight for the values that make our country unique - for the economic freedom that gives life to the American Dream.', 73911, 0), (498426, 'They were singing in French, but the melody was freedom and any American could understand that.', 16009, 0), (498427, 'Freedom is an internal achievement rather than an external adjustment.', 76316, 0), (498428, 'Being in Loyola College exposed me to other options and gave me confidence, apart from the freedom to bunk classes. I became a merchandiser and then a garment manufacturer, and interacting with foreign buyers and manufacturing foreign brands in India gave me a high.', 76317, 0), (498429, 'Pursuing your passion is fulfilling and leads to financial freedom.', 76318, 0), (498430, 'The most important influence in my childhood was my father.', 76319, 0), (498431, 'I love my dad, and I''m proud to be his daughter.', 76320, 0), (498432, 'My dad''s the one who''s always been there; he''s my hero, you could say. Even when he was working, he''d do anything for me. He''s been the biggest influence in my life.', 70758, 0), (498433, 'I think the most fun part about working on ''Good Luck Charlie'' is spending time with everyone, honestly, because everybody on set is like my brother and sister and mom and dad. They''re so fun to be around, so that''s probably the best part about working there.', 76321, 0), (498434, 'My dad always said, ''Champ, the measure of a man is not how often he is knocked down, but how quickly he gets up.''', 17532, 0), (498435, 'My Father had a profound influence on me. He was a lunatic.', 7873, 0), (498436, 'Dad is and always will be my living, breathing superhero.', 68250, 0), (498437, 'After my parents'' divorce when I was 4, I spent weekends with my dad before we finally moved to California. By the time Sunday rolled around, I was incapable of enjoying the day''s activities, of being in the moment, because I was already dreading the inevitable goodbye of Sunday evening.', 12642, 0), (498438, 'Everything I do in my life I do to make my mum and dad proud. I want to carry on in my dad''s footsteps and make sure that his legacy lives on forever.', 68250, 0), (498439, 'My dad, Frank Addison Albini, was a terrific shot with a rifle and had generally excellent hunting skills. While my dad loved hunting and fishing, he didn''t romanticize them. He was filling the freezer, not intellectualizing some caveman impulse or proving his worth as a real man.', 45603, 0), (498440, 'I inherited that calm from my father, who was a farmer. You sow, you wait for good or bad weather, you harvest, but working is something you always need to do.', 71190, 0), (498441, 'Dad was a baker, and we lived above the bakery, so I was always popping down to have an apple pie or a doughnut or a custard or gypsy tart: I had a very sweet tooth, and I think that that was what got me into doing what I do now.', 69750, 0), (498442, 'My father? I never knew him. Never even seen a picture of him.', 392, 0), (498443, 'Nowadays, if you have a mustache, people look at you like you''re crazy. But when I was growing up, I never saw my dad without a mustache.', 75822, 0), (498444, 'My father taught me that the only way you can make good at anything is to practice, and then practice some more.', 63429, 0), (498445, 'You know, my mother''s beautiful, my dad was a really handsome man, and there was a lot of talk about looks when I was growing up.', 68409, 0), (498446, 'I think there''s nothing better than laughing in life, so that''s nice, to be thought of as someone who can make someone laugh. It''s ''cause I think life is hard. You know, my dad was a really silly man. A great Irish silly man. And that''s fine.', 68513, 0), (498447, 'My mother told me, ''Always do your best,'' and my dad says, ''It''s important to be humble. That''s the key. They''re not there for you. You''re there for them.''', 76322, 0), (498448, 'I grew up watching my dad scout games live. They played on Saturday. Sometimes they wouldn''t get the films until Monday. Sunday air shipping from wherever the college team was located - Starkville, Mississippi, or wherever the film was coming from. It took two days.', 76323, 0), (498449, 'It is easier for a father to have children than for children to have a real father.', 4433, 0), (498450, 'I just wish I could understand my father.', 646, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498451, 'If my father had hugged me even once, I''d be an accountant right now.', 2319, 0), (498452, 'But my dad also was a remarkable man, a good person, a principled individual, a man of integrity.', 11458, 0), (498453, 'I like to keep most of my bats. I think I have about 250 bats, including my first - which cost Rs 2000 - a gift from my dad in 1998, when I moved to the hostel.', 67900, 0), (498454, 'Everyone talks about how we''re on our phones all the time, but the fact remains that when I''m away on a film set for two months, I can Skype my family. I remember the phone calls my parents had to make when my dad was away for a while when I was younger - that once-a-week expensive phone call! The time pressure on talking to your father!', 68286, 0), (498455, 'I actually hated hunting the first time I went when I was a kid. My dad took us deer hunting. We sat there for 30 minutes, and I felt like I was losing my mind. But in college, I fell in love with it. Football became a full-time job, and I needed an escape. I needed something that would mellow me out.', 69513, 0), (498456, 'Mental illness can happen to anybody. You can be a dustman, a politician, a Tesco worker... anyone. It could be your dad, your brother or your aunt.', 51929, 0), (498457, 'I never had a speech from my father ''this is what you must do or shouldn''t do'' but I just learned to be led by example. My father wasn''t perfect.', 68361, 0), (498458, 'My dad taught me from my youngest childhood memories through these connections with Aboriginal and tribal people that you must always protect people''s sacred status, regardless of the past.', 15778, 0), (498459, 'Simple. Pared down. Timeless. The ties were never too thick or too thin; the pants were never too flared or too skinny. In my life with Dad, he wore Western apparel because we went riding - jeans, cowboy boots, the turquoise belt buckle. But it was all very simple, and that classic look is very ''Ralph Lauren.''', 68368, 0), (498460, 'The lesson of Pearl Harbor ought never to be forgotten, and of course the motto that came from that, 69 years ago, the war which my dad fought, was ''Remember Pearl Harbor, never again.'' We need to keep that to mind.', 17647, 0), (498461, 'Most parents were, like, Little League coaches and all that. My dad was a wrestling fan. Instead of going out and playing home run derby with my old man, we just watched wrestling together.', 38715, 0), (498462, 'As Daddy said, life is 95 percent anticipation.', 49634, 0), (498463, 'Undeservedly you will atone for the sins of your fathers.', 2542, 0), (498464, 'Fathers are biological necessities, but social accidents.', 992, 0), (498465, 'I know that I will never find my father in any other man who comes into my life, because it is a void in my life that can only be filled by him.', 69081, 0), (498466, 'My grandfather, along with Carnegie, was a pioneer in philanthropy, which my father then practiced on a very large scale.', 73000, 0), (498467, 'I pressed my father''s hand and told him I would protect his grave with my life. My father smiled and passed away to the spirit land.', 4664, 0), (498468, 'Being a father, being a friend, those are the things that make me feel successful.', 67061, 0), (498469, 'A working definition of fathering might be this: fathering is the act of guiding a child to behave in ways that lead to the child''s becoming a secure child in full, thus increasing his or her chances of being happy and fruitful as a young adult.', 69169, 0), (498470, 'You can tell your uncle stuff that you could not tell your dad. That is kind of the role of an uncle. I feel very much like a father sometimes but sometimes I feel like a teammate.', 76324, 0), (498471, 'There are many people who are behind whatever I''ve achieved so far. My dad, Daboo Malik, is my mentor and guiding light who supported and influenced me. Without him, I wouldn''t have been able to be what I am today. Besides him, Salman Khan is yet another important person who is my biggest and constant inspiration.', 70661, 0), (498472, 'I was born in Orange County - in Santa Ana. My dad is from California. I was raised on the East Coast. My first two years were in California, but I claim East Coast. I''m sorry, I don''t rep California.', 71866, 0), (498473, 'I''m from Santa Cruz in Northern California, and the 49ers were my dad and I''s bonding time.', 69673, 0), (498474, 'My dad is a writer, and to see him always in front of a typewriter gave me the inspiration to write. He was my idol, my hero. I wanted to be just like him.', 67847, 0), (498475, 'My dad used to say, ''You wouldn''t worry so much about what people thought about you if you knew how seldom they did.', 68937, 0), (498476, 'As a brother and sister, our tastes were pretty different growing up. He liked a lot of early hip hop. My dad didn''t understand it and would try to talk him out of it.', 76325, 0), (498477, 'I''ve got high standards when it comes to boys. As my dad says, all girls should! I''m from the South - Tennessee, to be exact - and down there, we''re all about southern hospitality. I know that if I like a guy, he better be nice, and above all, my dad has to approve of him!', 682, 0), (498478, 'Within our culture, every school has a swimming pool. We lived on the coast. People swam in the surf. It''s a very sporty nation and at that particular time anyone who had an artistic bent was very much an outsider. So if you liked reading or ideas or playing the piano then your dad viewed you as a sissy, basically.', 72311, 0), (498479, 'We all have experiences in our lives that change us, and we all learn from people, like my dad, but at the end of the day, it''s only us. And we''re only responsible to make ourselves happy.', 66949, 0), (498480, 'I like to believe that I''ve got a lot of guardian warriors sittin'' on my shoulder including my dad.', 2110, 0), (498481, 'My dad became a soap opera actor, and I was an extra in a skating rink scene on the soap. I didn''t audition. It was nepotism all the way.', 883, 0), (498482, 'My dad''s method in his madness was to try every sport and then observe what I liked. I played football, tennis, golf, cricket but I loved my snooker.', 72088, 0), (498483, 'As a teenager, I developed a great interest in not only horse breeding but also horse racing and used to bet based on red-hot tips. I realized that becoming a bookmaker would be very lucrative, but Dad put his foot down, saying it was an inappropriate career.', 75622, 0), (498484, 'Growing up in Georgia, my dad was a farmer and we worked in agriculture, so we were always looking up at the sky, checking if rain was in the forecast. That always set the tone for the mood in my household, whether we had rain coming in or not - we knew the crops would be good and it was going to be a good week around the Bryan household.', 66563, 0), (498485, 'My dad was in the military. It was difficult sometimes, because he would have to be away a lot, and we would have to move around a lot. Trying to adapt to new schools and new places can be really tough.', 76326, 0), (498486, 'My dad was very intelligent, had a very strong personality. I was amazed with my father.', 63760, 0), (498487, 'My dad only ever talked about two things: bicycles and Mercedes.', 66984, 0), (498488, 'I hate short hair on men - the ''real'' man is something I don''t know. My dad was always playing with hairbands, making rings, while the women were wearing jeans, white T-shirts and Converse. That was the uniform at home.', 70722, 0), (498489, 'My dad being a salesman taught me you can sell anybody anything if you''ve got the ability to believe.', 2519, 0), (498490, 'When I was growing up, my parents were almost involved in various volunteer things. My dad was head of Planned Parenthood. And it was very controversial to be involved with that.', 1133, 0), (498491, 'Atticus Finch. That''s who I want to be when I grow up. He''s the greatest guy ever - a good dad, a good lawyer, doing the right thing. And he knows he''s not supposed to win, but he''s doing it anyway.', 76327, 0), (498492, 'I think, if I had a dad, I would have went the normal college route. I''m so stoked my life panned out how it was.', 19593, 0), (498493, 'My dad never missed a day of work, and he was always smiling when he came home.', 70245, 0), (498494, 'I''m so excited to be carrying on in Dad''s footsteps and making sure that everything he worked so hard for continues for the generations to come.', 68250, 0), (498495, 'I wanted to be a police officer for a long time so I could be just like my dad!', 60472, 0), (498496, 'Taylor was named after James Taylor and claims that she knows all the James Taylor songs, and I''m a huge fan of James Taylor and know all his songs, too. My dad told me that if I ever met Taylor Swift, I had to tell her that I know every James Taylor song. We started naming albums, and we were both shouting them out.', 69208, 0), (498497, 'I know my dad always wanted to heal the world, and so I think it would be great to follow in his footsteps.', 76320, 0), (498498, 'I was an all-sport athlete growing up. My dad, I think, hoped I would go to college on a scholarship.', 76328, 0), (498499, 'I didn''t come from a wealthy family. My dad told us if we wanted spending money, we had to earn it. So I developed an early work ethic.', 67634, 0), (498500, 'I''m compared to my dad all the time, and I''ve learned to take it positively by working hard.', 67033, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498501, 'I can remember 1987 when I had my first amateur fight in Michigan, weighing 64lb. I was 10 years old. I was the youngest and smallest guy on my team. I can remember what I ate. There was this restaurant called Ponderosa, and my dad made me eat a steak. I was happy. It was a first round knockout. I slept with my trophy for two weeks.', 67644, 0), (498502, 'My father was a tomato farmer. There is the phrase that says he or she worked their fingers to the bone, well, that''s my dad. And he was a very good man.', 11458, 0), (498503, 'Because of his military service, Dad was buried in Arlington National Cemetery.', 25693, 0), (498504, 'My dad knows how to tell a story. He''d make me laugh by doing all the different voices.', 47780, 0), (498505, 'My dad is a Chatty Cathy, the social butterfly; friendly; knows everybody in the whole world by six degrees; tells me that every performance is the greatest he''s ever seen, every new outfit is the coolest. Constant cheerleader.', 100, 0), (498506, 'My dad taught me never to be afraid of what''s on the other side of the mountain.', 66890, 0), (498507, 'Joanna points her camera at a section of society unused to having cameras pointed at it. But I don''t know about categorizing them in terms of class I''m a bit wary of that. My dad is the son of a shipbuilder. ', 1101, 0), (498508, 'I want to be a young dad. By 25 or 26 I want to see myself, like, married or start looking for a family.', 957, 0), (498509, 'My dad is very successful in his business. He''s always been big in having hobbies and having little ways to get away. He always made time for hunting and fishing. He always encouraged me to do it.', 66563, 0), (498510, 'When you''re growing up, your dad is your superhero. Once you''ve let yourself fall that in love with someone, once you put him on such a high pedestal and he lets you down, you never want to experience that pain again.', 8650, 0), (498511, 'My dad once said that in criminal law you see terrible people on their best behavior in family law you see great people on their worst behavior. ', 74221, 0), (498512, 'My brothers always like to believe that my father pampered me and I am spoilt. While it is not true, they felt that way. As for my dad, I could not do anything wrong. So, if I did something wrong, I would put the blame on them, and he would shout at them.', 67101, 0), (498513, 'To be able to have winning in your blood growing up, whether it was pounding my little brother or trying to beat my dad in something, or just competing on teams with my friends, it was nonstop.', 73377, 0), (498514, 'I was a pitcher, and my dad played in college. The hardest day of my life was telling him I was going to quit to focus more on golf. But with golf, I felt like the game can''t be perfected, and that motivated me.', 73377, 0), (498515, 'My dad actually makes the best cookies. My mum is great baker, too, but doesn''t share them - it''s tantalising! Luckily for me though, my dad shares his!', 38496, 0), (498516, 'With Dad, he was the ultimate wildlife warrior, and we admired him more than anything.', 68250, 0), (498517, 'I am a product of nepotism. I don''t think I would have had the profession that I''m in currently... if it wasn''t for my dad.', 67519, 0), (498518, 'Boxing''s in my genes. I come from a fighting background. My dad and both my uncles were good boxers. I''m blessed with the art of war.', 67644, 0), (498519, 'My story starts with my dad, a black boy born to a single mother in a small town in North Carolina. It starts with my parents meeting in Washington, D.C., in the ''60s, at a time of incredible activism.', 10615, 0), (498520, 'Growing up, I was discouraged from telling personal stories. My dad often used the phrase ''Don''t tell anyone.'' But not about creepy things. I don''t want to lead you down the wrong path. It would be about insignificant things. Like, I wouldn''t make the soccer team, and my father would say, ''Don''t tell anyone.''', 15814, 0), (498521, 'Whenever I fail as a father or husband... a toy and a diamond always works.', 7162, 0), (498522, 'My dad has always been really helpful. He taught me that talent is a bonus, but persistence is what wins out.', 75427, 0), (498523, 'My dad was the district attorney of New Orleans for about 30 years. And when he opened his campaign headquarters back in the early ''70s, when I was 5 years old, my mother wanted me to play the national anthem. And they got an upright piano on the back of a flatbed truck and I played it.', 68271, 0), (498524, 'I got stuck up a tree when I was about seven, and my dad had to come and get the ladder to get me down. I loved to climb all the way up to the top. I must have been a koala in my past life.', 18360, 0), (498525, 'Principles are the most important thing to me. One of the things I think my dad taught me was there are people who accept the world they live in and there are people who change the world they live in. I don''t accept my circumstances.', 70458, 0), (498526, 'My youngest son''s pre-school class was recently asked what their dads do for work. The responses were things like, my dad sells money, and my dad figures stuff out. My son said, ''I''ve never seen my dad do work.'' It''s true. Skateboarding doesn''t seem like real work, but I''m proud of what I do.', 54545, 0), (498527, 'The child is father of the man.', 2063, 0), (498528, 'My dad used to say, ''Just be yourself and you''ll be fine,'' but it''s really, really true.', 71011, 0), (498529, 'I started traveling by myself as early as 5 to see my dad. I''d go to Toronto or Los Angeles, depending on what show he was doing, but most often New York, and we would hang out, and he''d take me to museums and Broadway plays. The ones that had the biggest impact on me were the George C. Wolfe productions.', 69327, 0), (498530, 'I''ve never heard my dad say a bad word about anybody. He always keeps his emotions in check and is a true gentleman. I was taught that losing it was indulgent, a selfish act.', 43985, 0), (498531, 'My career choice is my career choice. Just stepping out of that zone, to be able to be a provider. I understand my position as a provider and my role as a dad also... Just being able to be comfortable with it.', 68174, 0), (498532, 'My dad is a motorcycle guy, not some Hollywood dude.', 66795, 0), (498533, 'My dad always taught me never to give up in my mind. You can never really beat me. It sounds ridiculous, but I will always come back for you. You can''t beat someone who never gives up. I could lose 100 times to you, but I will always get you. I will die trying. This applies not only to swimming but to my life as well.', 69792, 0), (498534, 'I was always a kid trying to make a buck. I borrowed a dollar from my dad, went to the penny candy store, bought a dollar''s worth of candy, set up my booth, and sold candy for five cents apiece. Ate half my inventory, made $2.50, gave my dad back his dollar.', 69247, 0), (498535, 'My first outdoor cooking memories are full of erratic British summers, Dad swearing at a barbecue that he couldn''t put together, and eventually eating charred sausages, feeling brilliant.', 15479, 0), (498536, 'My mum and dad aren''t together, but she plays a massive part in my life. We have deep conversations: I tell her where I need support, where I feel she''s lacking, and I support her with whatever she needs. I understand she won''t be here forever, and I want no regrets.', 68663, 0), (498537, 'My Dad, a small-town lawyer, was also named Paul. Until we lost him when I was 16, he was a gentle presence in my life. I like to think he''d be proud of me and my sister and brothers, because I''m sure proud of him and of where I come from, Janesville, Wisconsin.', 66572, 0), (498538, 'I didn''t have any role models really. My best friend was a dog. My mum and dad saved a dog from the gutter and that dog was my brother before Jesse was born. Sami was his name and he was my role model.', 69262, 0), (498539, 'Some of the happiest times I ever saw my dad was times when I was with him in the casinos, and he had a good night.', 76329, 0), (498540, 'One of the things my dad and I got to bond over was going to the San Antonio Spurs games when Gervin was there, James Silas... I can''t remember the rest of the guys'' names, but it was a fun time.', 36579, 0), (498541, 'As a father now, I wouldn''t do what my dad did, because it left me feeling emotionally unstable as a kid. But he didn''t do the things he did out of selfishness or malice.', 3498, 0), (498542, 'I want to stay healthy, keep fit, eat well, keep a low profile and be a good dad.', 51929, 0), (498543, 'One time, on Marine One, the president asked me my opinion. I had a flashback to being at the kitchen table with my dad. That dominant male figure set me up for being confident to express myself with precision and persuasion.', 61931, 0), (498544, 'I do remember vividly sometime after puberty when I''d answer the phone at home and the callers began to say, ''Hi, Bill!'' That''s when I knew Dad and I had the same voice.', 70639, 0), (498545, 'The biggest lesson I learned from my dad is to support children even if they''re doing something that is unorthodox.', 54545, 0), (498546, 'The worst advice I ever received from my dad was to play by the book.', 69271, 0), (498547, 'Humans have voids, and you need things to fill voids... I didn''t have a dad to fill that male model void, so when I heard Eminem or freaking seen Dave Chapelle, that''s what I gravitated to.', 19593, 0), (498548, 'My dad grew up in Banbridge, Northern Ireland, desperate to get to London. I grew up in London, so I don''t know what it''s like to yearn for the big city from a small town.', 1593, 0), (498549, 'Sons have always a rebellious wish to be disillusioned by that which charmed their fathers.', 1032, 0), (498550, 'I stopped loving my father a long time ago. What remained was the slavery to a pattern.', 23, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498551, 'I am lucky to have had an attentive, curious and loving dad and heart-smart, down-to-earth, gifted mother. They changed the outlooks of their own lives and have never forgotten the people and organizations that helped them dream bigger than their circumstances should have allowed.', 18389, 0), (498552, 'My dad liked to boil a squirrel head and suck the brains out the nose. Smaller than a chicken, bigger than a rat.', 28432, 0), (498553, 'Ah, my dad''s whistle. On holidays when I was a kid, we would all be off in the rock pools along the beach. When it came time to go, we''d hear the whistle and we''d all come running. Like dogs!', 22748, 0), (498554, 'I will always do what I can to help others, but when I retire, I want to be a dad and a husband. I want a house and a dog in the yard. I want to have barbecues.', 69347, 0), (498555, 'I didn''t know my dad for a long time. My dad was on drugs and my dad was at the VA Hospital, my dad was off in his own world selling drugs or using them or there would be crack heads in the house or whatever it would be.', 66795, 0), (498556, 'I have to remind my dad, ''Journalists - no matter how many cigars they smoke with you - are not your friends, so don''t talk to them.''', 45842, 0), (498557, 'My dad said to me growing up: ''When all is said and done, if you can count all your true friends on one hand, you''re a lucky man.''', 76330, 0), (498558, 'I was into the Mets because my Dad worked at IBM where he got free Mets tickets, so I was into the Mets... then I got to ''Saturday Night Live'' where my boss has unbelievable N.Y. Yankees tickets, so he invites us to the games. I''m going to all the games, so I might as well root for the team I''m gonna go sit with.', 61859, 0), (498559, 'My dad had an aunt at the turn of the century who died from diabetes, but she was the closest affected relative in my family.', 76331, 0), (498560, 'My mum was very conscious about fashion, and my dad was born into the tailoring tradition, so fashion has always been my life, although now, really, I wear the same thing - just in different weights - light and heavy cashmere in winter and cotton in summer. And jeans.', 67548, 0), (498561, 'I always joke that my kids'' favorite holiday is Father''s Day. They love the way I celebrate the occasion by writing each of them a thank-you letter and a generous check. It''s my way of letting them know how much I appreciate the great pleasure and privilege of being their dad.', 21729, 0), (498562, 'My family always helped me. I had people around me who always pushed me to be the best: my dad, my mum. My dad used to play and coach as well. But I wasn''t born with shiny things.', 76332, 0), (498563, 'My dad has been a big influence on me, because he''s always had his own business. He really taught me business sense and how to be a focused individual, but also how to have fun and make everyone around you have fun.', 1237, 0), (498564, 'On rare occasions, Dad used to reminisce about when he met Eisenhower and how Churchill would pop in, in the late hours of the evening or night, carrying a cigar, when he''d obviously had a good dinner.', 68428, 0), (498565, 'There''s sometimes a weird benefit to having an alcoholic, violent father. He really motivated me in that I never wanted to be anything like him.', 591, 0), (498566, 'A father is always making his baby into a little woman. And when she is a woman he turns her back again.', 31105, 0), (498567, 'I have never been a material girl. My father always told me never to love anything that cannot love you back.', 56084, 0), (498568, 'My father wants me to be like my brother, but I can''t be.', 74899, 0), (498569, 'Babies don''t need fathers, but mothers do. Someone who is taking care of a baby needs to be taken care of.', 74536, 0), (498570, 'I kept my babies fed. I could have dumped them, but I didn''t. I decided that whatever trip I was on, they were going with me. You''re looking at a real daddy.', 71751, 0), (498571, 'I was punished for blowing the whistle on my father''s lifestyle.', 75923, 0), (498572, 'When I was 18, I thought my father was pretty dumb. After a while when I got to be 21, I was amazed to find out how much he''d learned in three years.', 70420, 0), (498573, 'Since I was a boy, from this house, I was out rescuing crocodiles and snakes. My mum and dad were very passionate about that and, I was lucky enough to go along.', 15778, 0), (498574, 'Tiffany is very proud to have the last name and she''s proud of her dad.', 74740, 0), (498575, 'You know not having my real dad around and having a step dad made me want to be a great dad. So now I have been one for 9 years. And now 3 daughters. So, that is what I am - a dad, first and foremost, before anything else. It''s just something that comes natural now.', 6465, 0), (498576, 'I never saw any of my dad''s stories. My mother said he had piles and piles of manuscripts.', 578, 0), (498577, 'My dad saw my husband''s boss at a conference, and he said to stop paying my husband until we produce children.', 67514, 0), (498578, 'I said, ''Ooh, Dad, I want the yellow ones.'' He said, ''Where?'' I said, ''Right there, Dad. I want the yellow ones.'' Everybody goes, ''Those are green''. That''s how I knew I was colorblind.', 76333, 0), (498579, 'My dad never told me that when you audition, you might not get the role. He wanted to wait until my first disappointment to tell me.', 69521, 0), (498580, 'I would have to say the person with whom I am most in love is definitely my son, Everly Bear. Although I''m his dad, I''m also his friend.', 3498, 0), (498581, 'My mother wanted to name me Jackie or Jacqueline but she got to name my sister and my brother, so my dad and my brother insisted on naming me. And they were big fans of ''The Little Mermaid.''', 76334, 0), (498582, 'My dad''s a scratch golfer and I''ve got the knack of seeing something and then replicating it. I saw my dad swing a club and I worked out how to do the same thing. My backswing and follow-through have been basically the same since I was two.', 72004, 0), (498583, 'Now I meditate twice a day for half an hour. In meditation, I can let go of everything. I''m not Hugh Jackman. I''m not a dad. I''m not a husband. I''m just dipping into that powerful source that creates everything. I take a little bath in it.', 43985, 0), (498584, 'If anybody had a reason to become a delinquent, to become a criminal, to be angry at the man, to be angry at the white man, to be angry at America, it''s my dad, but he did not feel that way at all.', 55271, 0), (498585, 'During the Depression, my dad made radios to sell to make extra money. Nobody had any money to buy the radios, so he would trade them for dogs. He built kennels in the backyard, and he cared for the dogs.', 1377, 0), (498586, 'My mum was raised Jewish, my dad is very scientifically minded, and my school was vaguely Christian. We sang hymns in school. I liked the hymns bit, but apart from that, I can take it or leave it. So I had lots of different influences when I was younger.', 76335, 0), (498587, 'Paul McCartney had a baby when he was 61; Rod Stewart was 66; Rupert Murdoch was a stunning 72. Not only does that mean they''ll have less stamina than the average dad, that means they''ll, well, check out a lot sooner too.', 60048, 0), (498588, 'My mother played the piano and my father the violin, I can remember my dad teaching me how to waltz; I had my feet on his, my mother playing the piano, and my husband will tell you the lessons weren''t very successful.', 66941, 0), (498589, 'You draw the best things from your parents and family. You''re going to pick up some of the bad things as well - there''s a temper that runs through my dad''s side of the family that I''m not especially keen on picking up a giant block of.', 75422, 0), (498590, 'My dad''s quite a conservative person, and he brought me up to be very questioning of the commercial world. He looked down on pop culture. I definitely got the impression that pop was evil and that Britney Spears was evil.', 68466, 0), (498591, 'My mum and dad have always enjoyed life, and it''s something that''s been instilled in me. I wake up in a good mood most mornings.', 75807, 0), (498592, 'My mother was a very wonderful woman. When she and my dad divorced, she moved to California and worked two jobs in the cannery at night and as a waitress during the day. But she saved enough money to establish a restaurant.', 63760, 0), (498593, 'One of my dad''s friends from the music industry came over to our house one time and heard me sing, and he said, ''She should audition for this role I have!'' So I did! It was a movie called ''The Gospel,'' which I did when I was five. That was when I was like, ''I want to do this acting thing!''', 76336, 0), (498594, 'My dad was an assembly line worker at AC Spark Plug, which was a division of General Motors, and his job was to build and then inspect the little spark plugs as they came off the line.', 17499, 0), (498595, 'I love my dad; I''m a daddy''s girl, all the way.', 76337, 0), (498596, 'God bless Dad, he came to every one of my shows. I was bad, and I had horrible stage fright. My dad was so relieved - he''d say, ''You were terrible; this kid is not going to be an actor.'' Finally, I did a play and he said, ''Son - you were really good.''', 40335, 0), (498597, 'I remember my dad asking me one time, and it''s something that has always stuck with me: ''Why not you, Russ?'' You know, why not me? Why not me in the Super Bowl?', 70811, 0), (498598, 'I used to play chess when I was a kid and participate in national-level tournaments with the geekiest guys. This one time, I was losing terribly, so I batted my eyelashes and flirted as I asked for a draw. My dad just couldn''t believe it. He thought, ''What have I created, a floozy?'' But it worked!', 76338, 0), (498599, 'My dad''s cooking was magic in the kitchen. But eventually over the years, his personality changed and his ability to remember recipes failed. He became paranoid and thought people were stealing from him, when often he was just misplacing things.', 789, 0), (498600, 'Because my dad''s Chinese-American, and they''re very concrete, he said, ''There''s no money to be made in literature.'' So he told me to go into the sciences. And I was a good girl. And I did what Daddy said. And that''s how I ended up being a doctor. But you know, you just can''t stamp out that desire to tell stories.', 789, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498601, 'I recall my dad saying about me once that the only time he''d ever heard me say ''never'' was when I was asked if I''d had enough.', 75678, 0), (498602, 'My dad always taught me to never be satisfied: to want more and know that what is done is done. That was his way of seeing the game. You''ve done it, now move on. People might say, ''Well, when can you enjoy it?'' But it worked for me because, in the game, you need to be on your toes.', 68173, 0), (498603, 'I was obsessed with clowns. My dad had to get rid of them. I thought there were clowns under my bed for years.', 76339, 0), (498604, 'I had one of the most outdoorsy childhoods you could imagine. I basically lived in the woods until I was 13. My dad and I built a huge treehouse in our backyard in Chesterfield, about 30 feet in the air. And we''d vacation on an island in Michigan, where I hunted a deer that we ate.', 67604, 0), (498605, 'Wear what you want to wear. Do what you want to do. Be who you are. Pick out your own clothes. Be a man. And if that''s too much to ask, as it almost always is for me, think of someone you consider to be a man and pretend to be like him. I pretend to be like my dad.', 67648, 0), (498606, 'I''ve seen fathers criticizing their sons the moment a game''s over. Not my dad. It doesn''t matter if I threw an interception or a Hail Mary, he always says, ''Good job, son, I''m proud of you.'' Then he shakes my hand and gives me a hug. Every time.', 67693, 0), (498607, 'My dad set a clear model for me for what manhood was all about.', 10615, 0), (498608, 'M dad was a boxer, so he had this fierce, physical presence.', 67888, 0), (498609, 'I learned from my dad that change and experimentation are constants and important. You have to keep trying new things.', 76340, 0), (498610, 'I was looking for the meaning of life when I was in college. And my deal with my dad was as long as I was taking a full course load, then he would pay. And the times that I wasn''t taking a full course load, then I was off the dole and I was working.', 66656, 0), (498611, 'I''ve got the best parents you could ever ask for. My parents are from New Jersey, and they met in Vermont in college. My Dad grew up listening to heavy, psychedelic music. He''s my biggest fan.', 67550, 0), (498612, 'Every year, I give my dad an advance copy of my latest book. He reads it over the next several nights and says something incredibly supportive. Then he clears his throat nervously and changes the subject.', 18950, 0), (498613, 'I promised my dad before he passed away that I would take care of the family.', 76341, 0), (498614, 'One day we were sitting in our little classroom in the middle of Australia Zoo, and Dad bursts in and says, ''OK, today we''re going to go climb a mountain,'' - the Glass House Mountains are about 20 minutes away - so we packed up all our math work and ran out the door and climbed Mount Tibrogargan.', 68250, 0), (498615, 'There isn''t a dude outside my dad who had greater influence on my life.', 1309, 0), (498616, 'Had my dad not been short and fat and balding, there''s no doubt his career would have been very different. But he could do lots of stuff and made a very good career out of it. He had an incredible work ethic because he lost his father when he was very young, and the family had to pull together.', 66939, 0), (498617, 'If my dad was alive, I wouldn''t have gone to boarding school, and I wouldn''t have had the success I''ve had.', 66923, 0), (498618, 'I come from a very, very small town. There were no other actors around. I never met any actors. A lot of those times when I''d be out in the sheds with my dad, I''d step outside, and there''s just nothing out there but thousands of acres, forty thousand sheep, and miles of nothing. And so my mind would just wonder about what else was out there.', 72290, 0), (498619, 'I don''t think it ever occurred to me that I wouldn''t be an entrepreneur. My dad became a real estate developer, and that work is usually project-based. You attract investors for a project with a certain life cycle, and then you move on to the next thing. It''s almost like being a serial entrepreneur, so I had that as an example.', 69523, 0), (498620, 'I do have an occasional temper - I sort of inherited my dad''s short fuse.', 76342, 0), (498621, 'I never grew up on Jodeci. I never grew up on things like that ''cause my dad was a preacher, and he kind of kept us away from music like that.', 73209, 0), (498622, 'I''m definitely the super-cool dad.', 68262, 0), (498623, 'When you''re younger, you''re trying to understand and make sense of what your parents are trying to instill in you, which is ultimately life experience. I remember being 17 and my dad trying to teach me the importance of responsibility.', 67936, 0), (498624, 'I went through a brief phase when I thought of other career options: being an air hostess and even a psychologist. But eventually, my destiny led me to acting. Moreover, my dad being an actor, I have grown up in a very filmi environment. I was encouraged to watch films since I was a child.', 69775, 0), (498625, 'I''ve got a love affair with Harley-Davidson. One of my earliest photos with my dad is of him holding me as a baby on his bike.', 66798, 0), (498626, 'At my house, it''s an, ''If dad says it, you can say it'' kind of deal, so a lot of my slang words come off very childish at this point in my career.', 73165, 0), (498627, 'I have carried the burden of my dad''s image since day one. They never see me as just another guy trying to make his career in the film industry. I am always ''Megastar'' Chiranjeevi''s son first, and Ram Charan only later.', 67033, 0), (498628, 'My dad was always playing music. Not, like, playing music but listening to music.', 70208, 0), (498629, 'The most ironic thing is my grandfather has his masters in music composition; he was a jazz composer. My dad was a musician, too. He played more, like, soul music.', 69239, 0), (498630, 'I was homeless for about 8 months, I refused to live with my dad or anyone for that matter. So I stayed somewhere that had no hot water, ever, no heat, I told myself I have to be strong and get through it on my own.', 76343, 0), (498631, 'I was built up from my dad more than anyone else.', 1721, 0), (498632, 'My dad farmed, my granddad was a farmer. I wanted to be a farmer.', 72308, 0), (498633, 'My dad had been shortstop when he was in college, and you know, when you''re a kid, you want to be just like your dad.', 66702, 0), (498634, 'My dad would always say, ''What can you do to make the world a better place?'' Well, I can make people laugh.', 76344, 0), (498635, 'My father came from a very poor background, but I was very fortunate in the sense that we were never in need. My dad was determined to make sure that we didn''t want for things. He wanted to give us more opportunity than he had, a better shot at a better life.', 2614, 0), (498636, 'I remember when I was younger. Dad''s agent came round, and I asked if she would represent me. She didn''t represent children at the time, but I wouldn''t let her leave the house until she agreed. I''ve always been quite headstrong.', 76345, 0), (498637, 'You can''t be two people in your brain, one rock dude and a dad - there''s something in the middle of them, and that''s really what you are and that''s going to make you the best dad - not when you try to be one or the other.', 358, 0), (498638, 'Go on daddy-daughter dates and father-and-sons'' outings with your children. As a family, go on campouts and picnics, to ball games and recitals, to school programs, and so forth. Having Dad there makes all the difference.', 1826, 0), (498639, 'I was probably a terrible husband, but I pride myself on being a good dad.', 68367, 0), (498640, '''The Simpsons'' was about children and married parents; ''Futurama'' is about people in between; they''re growing up and haven''t settled down. Every other cartoon show seemed to be, you know, dumb dad, bratty kids.', 538, 0), (498641, 'My dad was a composer and a musician, but he never finished high school. His formal education was rather minimal from the standards of today''s college graduates and Ph.D.''s, but he had a deep interest in questions of science and questions of the universe.', 3476, 0), (498642, 'My dad gave me the gene to enjoy cooking, and to enjoy consuming good food and wine.', 66636, 0), (498643, 'I thank my dad for leaving me such a wonderful, wonderful heritage.', 68922, 0), (498644, 'I have a massive Samoan family. And the Samoan culture has always played a massive part of my life. I''ve got hundreds of family on my dad''s side that live in Samoa and in New Zealand. I''ve just been surrounded by the culture ever since I was a kid.', 76346, 0), (498645, 'Dad was an outstanding leader. He''d bring in top thinkers from a wide array of fields - how to fix the Detroit schools, for example. I watched him in these meetings. He listened and probed.', 52321, 0), (498646, 'When my dad founded our church, he used either a globe or a map of the world behind him. It was symbolic of what Christ said: to go forth and preach hope to the world. We believe in the cross, but we just continued with the globe.', 3956, 0), (498647, 'My dad loves what I do and I support my parents financially because they didn''t have a job that gave them a pension.', 2519, 0), (498648, 'My dad never graduated high school. He was a printing salesman. We lived in a two-bedroom, one-bath house in St. Louis Park, Minnesota. We weren''t rich - but we felt secure.', 11414, 0), (498649, 'OK, I have a nickname. My family calls me ''Trey'' because I''m William the third. My dad has the same name, which is always confusing because my dad is well known, and I''m also known.', 1133, 0), (498650, 'Me and my dad are the biggest promoters of an estate tax in the US. It''s not a popular position.', 1133, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498651, 'People are always coming up to me and saying, ''I heard your dad''s speech, and it''s really great.'' And they''ll mention some place I didn''t even know my dad was going to.', 1133, 0), (498652, 'The only advantage to being a middle-aged man is that when you put on a jacket and tie, you''re the Scary Dad. Never mind that no one has had an actually scary dad since 1966. The visceral fear remains.', 10731, 0), (498653, 'My dad had been born in Mexico and his family had to leave during the Mexican revolution.', 52321, 0), (498654, 'Because my dad abused me, I was determined to never let a man tell me what to do. God clearly showed me that I needed to be a submissive wife if I wanted to be effective in ministry. The truth is, if we don''t learn to submit to authority, we won''t ever learn to submit to God.', 1206, 0), (498655, 'My Dad used to tell us: ''En este pais, ustedes van a poder lograr todas las cosas que nosotros no pudimos'' ''In this country, you will be able to accomplish all the things we never could.''', 66707, 0), (498656, 'I remember one parent-teacher conference at the lower school, and Barack went, and there were SWAT guys on top of the roof of the school. And Malia was like, ''Dad, really? Really? Do they really have to be up there?'' And it''s like, yeah, honey, they do.', 1997, 0), (498657, 'My dad was fiscally conservative, and I was influenced by that. He didn''t believe in spending more than you had because it gets you into trouble.', 2269, 0), (498658, 'My dad was a big admirer of Sergeant York stories from the First World War.', 2269, 0), (498659, 'Ask anyone on Social Security if their check comes on time every month. Like clockwork. And it comes through the so-called dilapidated U.S. mail. My dad''s check literally will come on the same day every month. The government has been quite good and efficient at creating a number of systems.', 17499, 0), (498660, 'I wanted to be a skinny little ballerina but I was a voluptuous little Italian girl whose dad had meatballs on the table every night.', 47, 0), (498661, 'I love my daddy. My daddy''s everything. I hope I can find a man that will treat me as good as my dad.', 47, 0), (498662, 'Making your dad happy is - especially for an Italian Catholic girl, I''ll tell you - it feels really good.', 47, 0), (498663, 'I made a decision when my father passed away that I was going to be who God made me to be and not try to preach like my father.', 3956, 0), (498664, 'My dad had a church of 90 people when I was born. It was just, over the years it continued to grow.', 3956, 0), (498665, 'I didn''t try to copy my dad or fit into the pressure or the mold that everybody tried to make me fit into.', 3956, 0), (498666, 'My dad seemed comfortable with his decision to be a ''have-not,'' but I knew that I wasn''t.', 66592, 0), (498667, 'In 1997, in Rich Dad, Poor Dad, I stated, ''Your home is not an asset.'' Real estate agents sent me hate mail.', 66592, 0), (498668, 'When my book ''Rich Dad''s Prophecy'' was released in 2002, most financial newspapers and magazines trashed it because I discussed a looming stock market crash.', 66592, 0), (498669, 'My rich dad believed we should all learn to take care of ourselves.', 66592, 0), (498670, 'I think my dad has helped me tremendously.', 67555, 0), (498671, 'My dad was one of only four congressmen who supported Reagan.', 67555, 0), (498672, 'My dad got a job in a factory in Philadelphia, so I was raised in Germantown in a sort of a barracks for soldiers. They had housing for temporary housing. And then my parents saved money and bought a little house in South Jersey, built on a swamp.', 1883, 0), (498673, 'Working with my dad was such a gas. We approached the work in a similar way. We only made two films together when I was an adult, Tucker, and Blown Away, but it was so much fun to play with your parent like that.', 67519, 0), (498674, 'The first thing that pops into my mind when it comes to playing cowboys is my father, Lloyd Bridges. When I was a little kid, I loved to dress up like a cowboy - put on the boots, hat, and walk around. He was in a lot of westerns, and my dad loved to ride.', 67519, 0), (498675, 'My dad was very much a struggling actor and spent more of his life as a postman, as a member of a tarmac firm, as a van driver.', 22748, 0), (498676, 'Mum and Dad were very much friends and up for life. There was no anxiety for anything when I was growing up they just taught me to be me. ', 22748, 0), (498677, 'My dad would give me $10, which is a lot of money when you''re 9, to sing at church, on tables at restaurants, at family functions, just about anywhere.', 746, 0), (498678, 'My mother is very emotional as well, but my dad is more of the guts of the family. He was the main preacher, so he kind of had this little Pentecostal flair, but they are born-again.', 746, 0), (498679, 'My dad makes food with very few delicate flavours.', 47050, 0), (498680, 'Dad likes my food, but he probably thinks it''s too busy. He is a wonderful cook but only uses three ingredients. My mum rips out my articles and makes my recipes.', 47050, 0), (498681, 'My dad was never married. He was kind of a rolling stone. But he was never disrespectful. At the same time, even though he had women in his life when I was a kid, there wasn''t any consistency.', 44935, 0), (498682, 'My dad came from Cuba when he was a teenager not speaking English. And I grew up here speaking Spanglish. That''s the world in which I grew up, and that''s a world in which a lot of second generation immigrants find themselves.', 66992, 0), (498683, 'My dad grew up with an avocado tree in his backyard. My entire family, my wife and daughters, they love avocado. I may well be allergic. It makes me physically sick.', 66992, 0), (498684, 'This is going to sound horrible, but I don''t even know how much I make in a year. It must be, you know, a couple of million dollars, a few million. I know it''s more money than my dad, a jail guard, made in his lifetime; more money than I''ll ever need.', 9137, 0), (498685, 'I''m very at ease, and I like it. I never thought I would be such a family-oriented guy; I didn''t think that was part of my makeup. But somebody said that as you get older you become the person you always should have been, and I feel that''s happening to me. I''m rather surprised at who I am, because I''m actually like my dad!', 1232, 0), (498686, 'And I saw the sax line-up that he had behind him and I thought, I''m going to learn the saxophone. When I grow up, I''m going to play in his band. So I sort of persuaded my dad to get me a kind of a plastic saxophone on the hire purchase plan.', 1232, 0), (498687, 'My dad would go to work every day and write in a room full of funny people. He enjoyed it. I know great writers who find the process agonising but to me, writing has always been sheer joy.', 1099, 0), (498688, 'I have a son, but I''ve never had a daughter. I have a sister, and my sister had a fairly tempestuous relationship with my dad when she was young, and that was gripping and sometimes upsetting.', 4223, 0), (498689, 'You don''t want your children to look at you like you are anything special other than their dad.', 13073, 0), (498690, 'I wasn''t like a Fifties dad.', 13073, 0), (498691, 'People are so used to seeing John Goodman as a lovable dad or the quirky characters he played in the Coen Brothers films.', 69246, 0), (498692, 'People are so used to seeing John Goodman as a loveable dad or the quirky characters he played in the Coen Brothers films.', 69246, 0), (498693, 'The place of the father in the modern suburban family is a very small one, particularly if he plays golf.', 95, 0), (498694, 'The fundamental defect of fathers, in our competitive society, is that they want their children to be a credit to them.', 95, 0), (498695, 'I drove my mum and dad mad.', 71489, 0), (498696, 'My dad''s been responsible for a lot of my issues.', 5194, 0), (498697, 'I get that same queasy, nervous, thrilling feeling every time I go to work. That''s never worn off since I was 12 years-old with my dad''s 8-millimeter movie camera.', 5194, 0), (498698, 'My dad took me to my first movie. It was ''The Greatest Show on Earth'' in 1952, a movie of such scale it was actually a traumatic experience.', 5194, 0), (498699, 'I missed my dad a lot growing up, even though we were together as a family. My dad was really a workaholic. And he was always working.', 5194, 0), (498700, 'Dad entered the Second World War like any other man, trying to do the right thing.', 68428, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498701, 'I deal with my sons like young men. If they have a problem with something, they come to me. I am the type of dad that will drop everything I am doing for them, and always tell them to talk to me about it.', 68238, 0), (498702, 'My father was the role model I looked up to. My dad was an entertainer, too. I patterned my life after him. He wanted me to do better than he did. He never sold a record in his life, but to me, he was still a rock star.', 68238, 0), (498703, 'My dad was good with actions.', 30037, 0), (498704, 'My dad died of a stroke.', 30037, 0), (498705, 'Attraction doesn''t stop when a child is born. It''s the opposite. Being a mum and dad makes you even sexier.', 68239, 0), (498706, 'Think about finding out when you''re 13 that your dad is not your dad. It''s like, okay, take it on the chin and keep going. No choice, really.', 68239, 0), (498707, 'I was in the bath at the time, and my dad came running in and said, ''Guess who they want to play Harry Potter!?'' and I started to cry. It was probably the best moment of my life.', 1593, 0), (498708, 'My dad''s got a brilliant eye for scripts ''cos he''s a literary agent. He and my agent read a load of scripts and filter them.', 1593, 0), (498709, 'When I was 13, I opened my own business called The Awesome Pretzel Company, and my dad helped me build a pretzel cart.', 69247, 0), (498710, 'I think my dad is highly gender-neutral. If he doesn''t like someone, he''ll articulate that, and I think it''s also part of what resonates about him. He''ll say what he''s thinking.', 26172, 0), (498711, 'It was my dad''s idea to change my name from Sahatciu to Ora. He said it would be easier to pronounce.', 68240, 0), (498712, 'My mum and my dad are the sweetest couple.', 68240, 0), (498713, 'My dad wanted me to go down a more academic route. He is very much about sticking to the rule book and sticking to the blueprint of a successful career.', 68240, 0), (498714, 'I love eating at my dad''s pub, the Queens Arms in Kilburn. It does a traditional Albanian spinach pie.', 68240, 0), (498715, 'My dad took on every job he could get. He worked like mad. But then, at some point, he had saved up enough to open his first pub.', 68240, 0), (498716, 'I''ve been going to Bicester Village since I was young. My mum and dad really loved that place, and I always used to stock up on clothes. I love the fact that it supports great British designers.', 68240, 0), (498717, 'Now my dad is with me, traveling with me and a big part of this whole thing is I like to mix it up a little bit, you know. Who gets to take their father on a private jet across the country and stay in first class hotels? So we''re enjoying it, but I''d stop if it''s not possible.', 66795, 0), (498718, 'I don''t know, I just want to be happy. I could be in a hole somewhere. Or I could completely lose it and be some hippy living in the woods with my dad.', 66795, 0), (498719, 'I''m not great at dealing with death, I have to say. I find death very hard: my mum, my dad, Sid Vicious. I''m not a monster; I feel it and it scares me. One death at a time, please, is all my heart will bear.', 14227, 0), (498720, 'I truly think comedy is - being funny is DNA. My dad was a doctor, a wonderful doctor, and people still come up to me today, ''Your father helped my mother die.'' You know what I''m saying? He made her laugh ''til she died. My father was always very funny.', 17330, 0), (498721, 'I stayed in Baghdad every summer until I was 14. My dad''s sister is still there, but many of my relatives have managed to get out. People forget that there are still people there who are not radicalized in any particular direction, trying to live normal lives in a very difficult situation.', 69023, 0), (498722, 'My mother had very humble beginnings - to put it mildly. Her dad built their home out of timber that he cut down on their land. No heat, no air-conditioning - ''no foolishness,'' as he would call it.', 38496, 0), (498723, 'My dad was an English professor.', 38496, 0), (498724, 'Great dad. Yeah, he would ask me for money on birthdays and, you know, inappropriate times. And I just wrote him off like, ''You''re not a father.'' I just learned you cannot emotionally invest in people who are not attainable.', 292, 0), (498725, 'I used to do bell ringing in Benenden church. It was really good fun, actually. My best friend''s dad was the local vicar, and so it was expected as her best friend that I would go to church every Sunday with her.', 17159, 0), (498726, 'My dad''s a very sensitive man, but as the archetypal rebellious teenager, I didn''t realise that.', 17159, 0), (498727, 'My mum is bright, ambitious, well read, political and very bolshie: when my dad was conscripted into the Army and posted to Libya, she convinced some general to let her go with him. I don''t know how she managed it.', 17159, 0), (498728, 'It wasn''t like I was self-motivated. My dad started me. It was his dream before it was mine.', 37889, 0), (498729, 'I''m always on the court with my dad.', 37889, 0), (498730, 'My dad loves to eat, and he loves everything I make!', 37889, 0), (498731, 'My views about God come from my dad. Dad told me that he believed Nature, which to him included humankind, to be so beautiful, so magnificent, that there had to be something behind it all.', 11414, 0), (498732, 'My parents didn''t make a lot of money. My dad was not a high school graduate - he didn''t have a career as such he was a printing salesman essentially for most of his working life. ', 11414, 0), (498733, 'My dad loved comedians, especially George Jessel, and he loved Henny Youngman and Buddy Hackett.', 11414, 0), (498734, 'My dad was a terrible businessman.', 11414, 0), (498735, 'My dad is an attorney. I''ve always been interested in it. My sons are probably going to law school.', 12642, 0), (498736, 'A kid is something precious, and you want to protect it and keep it fun. I''m not a dad, but I''ve seen people and how they behave with their kids.', 68421, 0), (498737, 'When I was growing up, my dad didn''t have weights, so he made himself a weight bench. Instead of a hand-me-down jacket, it was a hand-me-down weight bench.', 68421, 0), (498738, 'The physical DNA has always been part of our family. My dad was a good boxer and gymnast; my mum is a ballroom dancer, and my brother does martial arts.', 68421, 0), (498739, 'I remember tap-dancing and singing in front of the TV when I was a kid, telling my dad to stop watching Ed Sullivan or Milton Berle and watch me.', 67003, 0), (498740, 'In my heart, I''m just a kid from the council houses. I can remember the old cottage and my dad coming round with the tin bath. I''m not a rich man.', 195, 0), (498741, 'Mickey Rourke''s character in ''The Wrestler'' - that was my dad, that was my uncles, that was so many members of my family. It was the only thing they knew. And then they would end up wrestling for a hundred bucks, go to autograph signings for two hundred bucks.', 11331, 0), (498742, 'When I was a kid at four years old, that''s when I started amateur wrestling with my dad and family. And when that''s instilled in you, it never goes away.', 11331, 0), (498743, 'I had a very strict upbringing with my dad and was very close to my mum, who was extremely loving.', 1549, 0), (498744, 'I love my dad. There is no doubt about that. He is a wonderful man and a good person. Like many father/son relationships, we have our struggles, our misunderstandings, and our miscommunications. We are very different people, but also very similar at the same time.', 69298, 0), (498745, 'I would say the dumbest thing I have heard is that my dad isn''t my real dad.', 66708, 0), (498746, 'If your dad died before you were born, yeah, it hurts - but it''s not like you had a connection with something that was real. Not to say it''s any better - but to have that connection and then have it ripped away was, like, the worst. My dad was such a good dad that when he left, he left a huge scar. He was my superhero.', 8650, 0), (498747, 'My dad was president of the volunteer fire department, which was within walking distance to our house. I spent several days of each week there with him - any time the whistle blew, he went. It was truly inspiring to watch him lead that way.', 34097, 0), (498748, 'My dad was a preacher.', 11679, 0), (498749, 'My dad always used to encourage me to dress weird.', 60194, 0), (498750, 'My career plan at this point is ''Ice Age 5'' through ''10,'' and even ''12,'' and ''Spider Man'' - you know, basically I''d be Emma Stone''s dad for the rest of my career. I really don''t have any problem doing that.', 17500, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498751, 'My grandmother was an actress too. In the thirties and forties she was under contract with Universal Studios. Crazy credits, lots of them. My dad was also under contract with Universal Studios. And my first film was shot on the same stage they both worked on at Universal.', 12497, 0), (498752, 'I think my dad is the only Arabic descendent who is an unsuccessful businessman.', 67847, 0), (498753, 'At the age of eight, I discovered that I could write songs. My dad used to take them to the notary and register them so that nobody could steal them from me.', 67847, 0), (498754, 'The thing is, my dad''s always been more of a bookworm; he was interested in more intellectual pursuits, but nobody can escape the passion that football stirs.', 67847, 0), (498755, 'I adore my dad. He''s a 78-year-old man and my inspiration.', 67847, 0), (498756, 'My dad was a slightly stricter version of Richard Dawkins. The worldview was that there are idiots out there who believe in Santa Claus and fairies and magic and elves, and we''re not joining that nonsense.', 639, 0), (498757, 'My favorite thing about ''Saturday Night''s Main Event,'' it was that one time where I could stay up late with my dad and four brothers, and we would all beat the tar out of each other while the show was on, and it was all okay because my dad was a wrestling fan.', 38715, 0), (498758, 'When I was a boy, my own dad told me in a smiling and wistful way that it''s a wise man that knows his own father.', 10407, 0), (498759, 'My dad and I are best friends. He''s pretty much responsible for the way I turned out. He would provide a little artistic inspiration here and there in the form of a guitar, stuff like that.', 60178, 0), (498760, 'My dad is an egomaniac.', 68242, 0), (498761, 'What I think is remarkable about my mum and dad is they had no interest in films, really. None.', 3497, 0), (498762, 'My dad always told me that the principal reason he chose New Zealand to emigrate to after World War II was the high regard his father had for the Kiwis he encountered at Gallipoli.', 3497, 0), (498763, 'My dad goes through war novels like I go through boxes of Cinnamon Toast Crunch.', 15814, 0), (498764, 'All the learnin'' my father paid for was a bit o'' birch at one end and an alphabet at the other.', 215, 0), (498765, 'I know that my dad not being in my life made a huge impact on me.', 67850, 0), (498766, 'When I was about 12 years old back in Houston, my Dad used to take us to the driving range.', 1252, 0), (498767, 'My dad believed in scaring us as we were growing up. Scaring the boys who wanted to date us more.', 28327, 0), (498768, 'I busted my chin open trying to be Evel Knievel on my bike. When it happened, you could see straight through to the bone, I thought my dad was going to pass out. It left a scar that I still have now.', 28327, 0), (498769, 'If you''re a girl, you''re always Daddy''s little girl. You''re vulnerable, no matter how worldly or sophisticated or strong you''d become along the way. My dad Lionel let me know how proud he was, even as he kept me from being too big for my britches.', 67006, 0), (498770, 'Our public portrayal of fathers has shifted during my life. TV fathers have ''evolved'' from real people like Sheriff Andy Taylor, Beaver''s dad Ward Cleaver and Heathcliff ''Cliff'' Huxtable, to cartoon dads like Homer Simpson and Seth MacFarlane''s caricatures in ''American Dad!'' and ''Family Guy.''', 67006, 0), (498771, 'I have to say that my dad''s face is very malleable. He''s barely got any cartilage in his face. I think I maybe inherited that Play-Doh-like physicality from him.', 70251, 0), (498772, 'When I was 13, I had my first job with my dad carrying shingles up to the roof. And then I got a job washing dishes at a restaurant. And then I got a job in a grocery store deli. And then I got a job in a factory sweeping Cheerio dust off the ground.', 20099, 0), (498773, 'My dad was young; he went to work. But he''d been to war. He''d seen some of the world. It wasn''t like he was going to be an extensive traveler or something. It didn''t seem to be in his nature or in the nature of his parents or many of the folks in my family, really.', 2251, 0), (498774, 'I think I created my particular stage persona out of my dad''s life, and perhaps I even built it to suit him to some degree.', 2251, 0), (498775, 'Once, I was coming back from school, and there was this guy who was eve-teasing me and my friend. I had a Milton water bottle that I flung it at his face. My dad told me if you are in a crowded place and a guy eve-teases, you should make noise. I did exactly that and got people on the road to beat up the guy.', 66951, 0), (498776, 'My dad taught me to never be pigeonholed to really allow yourself to reinvent characters as they reinvent you to be bold and to be willing to play seemingly unlikeable people. ', 68913, 0), (498777, 'My dad was always interested in characters he didn''t understand - he was such a great bad guy in movies. And that is really the thing that calls me to the material often: something I struggle to understand in human behaviour.', 68913, 0), (498778, 'To stay true to your art is such a complicated journey, and Dad clearly has done it.', 68913, 0), (498779, 'I started school in public housing. My dad had a sixth-grade education.', 68244, 0), (498780, 'I remember my dad working with me on breaking down my script and writing out a back story for my character and all that stuff.', 58696, 0), (498781, 'My father was a writer/director/producer, so instead of throwing a ball around, our bonding was going to see movies. And at an early age, I knew if I wanted to impress my dad, it was not going to be by throwing a ball real far.', 58696, 0), (498782, 'You, Dad, in the large scheme of things, don''t matter. I, Dad, don''t matter. We''re vectors on the grids of cellular life.', 9680, 0), (498783, 'I''ve always loved video games. I played ''Ms. Pac-man'' with my dad, and I Ioved ''Galaga'' and ''Tempest'' and grew up on the standing arcade games. Even to this day, my dad will call me if he''s playing ''Ms. Pac-man'' and hold the phone up to the game.', 61882, 0), (498784, 'My dad, he was a construction worker. He was a butcher. He was a deep sea fisherman.', 61882, 0), (498785, 'I was raised by a single dad, and I''ve always kind of liked things that are typically more guy-oriented.', 61882, 0), (498786, 'I was raised by a single dad. Dad''s idea of hanging out with your kid or day care was give her $20 in quarters, drop her at the arcade, and tell her not to talk to strangers.', 61882, 0), (498787, 'My dad was a big Frank Zappa fan, so I remember listening to a lot of Frank Zappa. Girls do not like Frank Zappa.', 69326, 0), (498788, 'It''s a complex relationship when your dad happened to be president and you are president and then you have all the amateur psychology that goes on when people try to speculate about motivations.', 68245, 0), (498789, 'I think my dad''s post-presidency, he didn''t miss a beat. He didn''t get into any kind of ''Woe is me.'' He dusted himself off and led an incredible life since 1993.', 68245, 0), (498790, 'I think it was hard at first for my dad to transition to being immobile.', 68245, 0), (498791, 'Shout-out to my dad - he influenced my style when I was 17.', 67009, 0), (498792, 'I remember in the fifth grade my dad would take me to Manhattan to shop for clothes.', 67009, 0), (498793, 'The first time I went to New York, I went with my first boyfriend, Clark. His dad had just bought an apartment in New York, and my dad dropped us off, and we were there for a week on our own. I must have been 15 or 16. I remember I went to Harlem and bought a goose jacket. That was the hip, hot thing.', 12807, 0), (498794, 'My dad had a Vincent Black Shadow, which was a quite particular thing: it was the fastest cycle of its era... It sparked a world for me; when I was old enough, I got a motorcycle.', 18599, 0), (498795, 'I have my dad''s shape. No booty.', 10195, 0), (498796, 'All that really matters is I have two beautiful kids, and I''m trying to be the best dad I can possibly be, and that''s the most important thing of all.', 11163, 0), (498797, 'When I started writing, I did have some idealised notion of my dad as a writer. But I have less and less of a literary rivalry with him as I''ve gone on. I certainly don''t feel I need his approval, although maybe that''s because I''m confident that I''ve got it.', 1979, 0), (498798, 'Overcoming my dad telling me that I could never amount to anything is what has made me the megalomaniac that you see today.', 1397, 0), (498799, 'I''m more comfortable with whatever''s wrong with me than my father was whenever he felt he failed or didn''t measure up to the standard he set.', 18212, 0), (498800, 'When I was little, my dad used to call me ''Bandarella,'' because I was a mess - a Bandar is a monkey in Hindi. I was not a girly-girl and would always break something and would be running around and didn''t really fit in.', 71665, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498801, 'My dad had a lot of bad luck. You could see his suffering, his terrible suffering, living a life that was disappointing and looking for another one.', 9118, 0), (498802, 'My old man tried to force on me a notion of what it was to be a ''man.'' And it destroyed my dad.', 9118, 0), (498803, 'People have told me, ''My dad passed on, but I have great memories of watching your shows with him.'' It doesn''t get any better than that.', 51805, 0), (498804, 'My dad died of a heart attack when I was 15. I was bullied mercilessly in middle school. I went through a divorce - those not-so-great things are all a part of me, and they give me a place to go when I cover those stories on the news. I''m more empathetic, more relatable because of them.', 8452, 0), (498805, 'My dad always said that hard work beats talent when talent doesn''t work hard enough.', 72053, 0), (498806, 'I didn''t start sweating until I had children. That was one of the first things I realized when my daughter Violet was born - I started getting wicked BO. You know there''s a difference between basketball BO and stress BO? This was definitely stress BO. Like, new dad BO.', 22301, 0), (498807, 'My mother taught me what it is to have a sense of humour; my dad, who was a headmaster, everything you need to know about hard work. My dad is the most decent man you could come across.', 68918, 0), (498808, 'I grew up upper-class. Private school. My dad had a Jaguar. We''re African-American, and we work together as a family, so people assume we''re like the Jacksons. But I didn''t have parents using me to get out of a bad situation.', 1525, 0), (498809, 'My dad was in the Second World War with General Patton. He won medals for bravery, but he came home quite damaged, so he was a handful. He told us some terrible stories, and I guess you''d say he suffered from post-traumatic stress disorder.', 65023, 0), (498810, 'My dad designed houses and was an architect for many years.', 69730, 0), (498811, 'My dad was the way he was, but he also gave me a motto: never say die. Just to keep pushing and pushing, fighting until the end. He put it in my head that you''re always going to fight, and you''re always going to beat them.', 66923, 0), (498812, 'My dad was a violent alcoholic. Really aggressive.', 66923, 0), (498813, 'When you lose someone whose life was so extraordinary like my dad''s, you have two options: You can curl up in a dark corner... or rise above it and dust yourself off and continue with their work. He will always be with me.', 68250, 0), (498814, 'I''m concerned a little bit with the culture of celebrating the fundraise. My dad taught me that when you borrow money it''s the worst day of your life.', 11355, 0), (498815, 'When I was three years old, my dad bought me my first drum set.', 69239, 0), (498816, 'There is too much fathering going on just now and there is no doubt about it fathers are depressing.', 1267, 0), (498817, 'My grandfather and my uncle both died from colorectal cancer, my dad almost died from it and I have the gene for it.', 19298, 0), (498818, 'I am very close to my brother Ramesh Babu. When my father was away for shootings, my brother would take care of me, and I am very close to him, and yes, Dad''s always special. He used to call me and enquire about my film''s progress. Whenever I deliver a hit, I can see a glow on my father''s face.', 68920, 0), (498819, 'My dad was a labour lawyer, and the ideas that I grew up with - bad management, bad capitalism, robber barons - when I applied this to my own life, I saw that we are all on both sides of the coin.', 2221, 0), (498820, 'My dad was an immigrant kid and a Democrat and a Jew, and we didn''t know any Republicans in our group. So I grew up Democratic. My dad was a labor lawyer - a very hardworking guy, a one-horse labor lawyer - and then I went to hippie college and lived in the bubble.', 2221, 0), (498821, 'I was raised by free-spirited people, though my father gave me a very strong work ethic.', 67021, 0), (498822, 'My greatest dream is to work with my dad someday as an actress.', 68921, 0), (498823, 'My dad made a film called ''Willow'' when he was a young filmmaker, which screened at the Cannes film festival, and people were booing afterwards.', 68921, 0), (498824, 'I don''t think my kids have to worry too much about me embarrassing them because that''s not how I would want to grow up, with wacky dad showing up at school and performing for everyone.', 47094, 0), (498825, 'My father was grounded, a very meat-and-potatoes man. He was a baker.', 48587, 0), (498826, 'My life is black and white and mixed. My mother''s a Rastafarian, my dad was a short white guy - it''s not an affectation. It''s also the lives of millions of people throughout the world.', 825, 0), (498827, 'I still love recording and still love the stage, but like my dad, I have the most fun when I am in front of that glorious orchestra or that kick-butt big band.', 68922, 0), (498828, 'My dad cut my hair once - I wanted a bob and he gave me a bowl cut. That was a tough few years.', 45044, 0), (498829, 'My dad has kind of been the standard for me, he played 16 years in the league, and since I''ve been in the league, every year that I go through and deal with the scratches, the bumps and bruises, just the grind that it is to go through one NBA season.', 69121, 0), (498830, 'But I have to be careful not to let the world dazzle me so much that I forget that I''m a husband and a father.', 30074, 0), (498831, 'I don''t think I can boast about him. ''Hey, my dad is a British institution; he''s done all these incredible things and I''m really proud of him.'' There is a certain baggage that comes with that in England.', 68436, 0), (498832, 'Everybody wanna be a super dad and the best dad ever, but sometimes, I''m just realizing that I''m not perfect.', 68174, 0), (498833, 'My mum is really fair and has blonde hair, and my dad is not dark, either.', 69348, 0), (498834, 'Mum and Dad met campaigning on the Spanish civil war. Both were active peace campaigners. They died in 1986 and ''87.', 50602, 0), (498835, 'My dad takes care of me as a manager and as a dad. That''s his job, you know, to take care of me. He has my best interests at heart.', 52064, 0), (498836, 'I went to see England against Switzerland at Wembley with my dad and brother, too. That was in 2008, Fabio Capello''s first game in charge. Jermaine Jenas scored, and we won 2-1. I remember the national anthem was incredible. I sang it with pride - always do.', 75689, 0), (498837, 'My dad was a truck driver, and from the time I was knee high to a grapevine, I was driving a truck.', 67029, 0), (498838, 'My dad was a truck driver. We all used to ride along with him. And the way he''d keep awake was to sing while he was going down the road. So we all joined in.', 67029, 0), (498839, 'I grew up in Birmingham, but my parents are originally from Barbados. My dad, Romeo, was a long-distance lorry driver, and my mother, Mayleen, worked in catering.', 70638, 0), (498840, 'My dad turned me onto Peter Sellers as a kid. I loved the fact that he was a unique combination of being extremely subtle and over-the-top all at the same time, and that''s a hard thing to do. I admire that.', 67411, 0), (498841, 'My dad got me a huge board when I was little. He loves to surf. He suited me up and sent me out on this huge wave. I went under, and when I came out and the board hit me in the face. So I said, I never wanted to do this again. I stayed away until I was 13.', 67034, 0), (498842, 'People say, ''You will be 30 years old; you''re too old. You''ll get your nose broke,'' say dad''s a pushy dad. You hear stupid things and put them out of your mind.', 69734, 0), (498843, 'My dad''s one true quest in life was for the Platonic ideal of peanut butter. And I remember one day he announced, with a look of utter transfiguration on his face, that he had found paradise on Earth in a jar with a yellow cap. And it was called Red Wing.', 20608, 0), (498844, 'My dad was a pastor, so we were in church all the time.', 69736, 0), (498845, 'I remember taking my stabilisers off my bike with my dad in the back garden. It was a small little bike, and it was called Poppy, had balloons on it, and was purple.', 69737, 0), (498846, 'Where I come from, you don''t really talk about how much you''re earning. Those things are private. My dad never told my mum how much he was earning. I''m certainly not going to tell the world. I''m doing well.', 67, 0), (498847, 'My dad was a particularly polite kind of guy, very courteous.', 67, 0), (498848, 'When I first joined SAG, there was another John Reilly. My dad was John Reilly, too, but growing up I was John John. Nobody in life calls me John C. It''s more like, ''Hey you, Step Brother!''', 70258, 0), (498849, 'I think I got into travelling because it was so not in my blood, so against my tendency to just stay put because my dad just hated going on holidays, because, as I''ve said in many essays, the thing that he hated more than anything else in life was spending money. And as soon as you leave your home, you''re spending money.', 9638, 0), (498850, 'In Brazil, if you have a son, the first thing you give him is a football. That''s the first gift - so my dad was no different.', 71244, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498851, 'It''s weird, the idea of someone else playing my dad, but weirdly nice.', 67051, 0), (498852, 'My dad is the nicest guy you''ll ever meet, and the easiest going.', 70497, 0), (498853, 'Feels good to try, but playing a father, I''m getting a little older. I see now that I''m taking it more serious and I do want that lifestyle.', 68361, 0), (498854, 'My dad was a roofer when I was young. I believe he owned his own roofing company in Florida. And then he fell through a roof, broke his back. Permanently. I mean, he''s not paralyzed or anything, but he''s had to deal with pain for all of his life since then.', 68275, 0), (498855, 'We came to Portland because there was a good alternative public school. Friends who lived there told me about it, and my son loved it. I left his dad and went to work slinging hash in a breakfast diner and working nights tending bar in a biker tavern.', 3175, 0), (498856, 'I love the comic opportunities that come up in the context of a father-son relationship.', 12392, 0), (498857, 'I wanted to be a forest ranger or a coal man. At a very early age, I knew I didn''t want to do what my dad did, which was work in an office.', 12392, 0), (498858, 'When I was little, we had a Golden Book that had all these Disney characters in one portrait on the first page. My dad used to read from it every night. We''d play this game of find Pluto or find Donald Duck. He''d read us stories and do all the voices. Those are great memories.', 66799, 0), (498859, 'But I honestly don''t read critics. My dad reads absolutely everything ever written about me. He calls me up to read ecstatic reviews, but I always insist that I can''t hear them. If you give value to the good reviews, you have to give value to the criticism.', 15776, 0), (498860, 'I grew up with a truck. My dad had one, so I like trucks.', 68279, 0), (498861, 'I have four shelves covered with journals that I''ve written. Dad and I are writing songs together. I''ve probably written 100 songs.', 682, 0), (498862, 'My parents are very hard working people who did everything they could for their children. I have two brothers and they worked dog hard to give us an education and provide us with the most comfortable life possible. My dad provided for his family daily. So, yes, that is definitely in my DNA.', 70676, 0), (498863, 'My father, he was like the rock, the guy you went to with every problem.', 18099, 0), (498864, 'I feel my dad, I still feel his love, and I still love him. I would do anything to have him back, but half the reason that my life is good, has real, true value, is that he died. I would obviously rather have him alive, but he gave me so much in his death.', 18099, 0), (498865, 'I want to be a dad. That''s floating to the top of my list. I think it''s such an important thing. I''m at the age where everyone has kids, and I ask them, ''Is it like a puppy?'' And they go, ''It''s 10 times a puppy.''', 61859, 0), (498866, 'An angry father is most cruel towards himself.', 2904, 0), (498867, 'I want my kids to see me as Dad, for God''s sake, not a television personality.', 49687, 0), (498868, 'I think some of my darkness comes from my dad. There is definitely convict history on that side of the family, a lot of dodginess. But with the darkness can also come entrepreneurialism, genius traits.', 67065, 0), (498869, 'My dad worked two jobs and moved us to the suburbs, and just being a black person, I went through a lot of racism and being called names and being bullied every single day. And it was hard. I didn''t have any friends.', 73210, 0), (498870, 'A dramatic thing, the first time you stand up to your dad.', 68285, 0), (498871, 'My dad was diagnosed with cancer, so we ended up burying him a year to the day that he was diagnosed.', 68360, 0), (498872, 'Child-rearing is my main interest now. I''m a hands-on father.', 3185, 0), (498873, 'I''m an ambassador for the Make-A-Wish Foundation, and one of the children, his wish was to go to the Emmys, so he''s going to be my date, along with my husband, and my dad and his girlfriend. So we''re going to have a really fun night and it''s going to be really exciting. I''m really excited for him to experience that.', 73211, 0), (498874, 'My dad studies and practices homeopathy and Ayurveda medicine. He''s a strong believer in both honey and milk as forms of healing. Honey is the one food that does not die. It does not expire. Growing up, he''d always be mixing up almonds or turmeric or gram flower with milk to cure a cough or a cold.', 694, 0), (498875, 'I was always embarrassed because my dad wore a suit and my mother wore flat pumps and a cozy jumper while my friends'' parents were punks or hippies.', 28855, 0), (498876, '''Dirt On My Boots'' is a very different song. I heard the melody, and I heard the lyrics, and I heard the drive of that song. I totally related. It was kinda me when I was on my bulldozer working for my dad.', 67876, 0), (498877, 'My dad was in the military, yeah. He was in the Air Force, and he was a doctor, so he would go places for six months here, and two years there. And I was home-schooled because I played the violin, and I did a lot of competitions.', 2287, 0), (498878, 'When I turned 11, my dad decorated a room at the Standard hotel in Los Angeles in a ''60s, Austin Powers style. There was human bowling: You run inside a giant inflatable ball and try to knock down pins. To this day, adults say it was one of the craziest parties they''ve ever been to.', 68464, 0), (498879, 'I mean, my dad''s a television producer, and I knew I could get a job as an assistant or a reader with one of his friends, but it wasn''t exactly what I wanted to do.', 32870, 0), (498880, 'Mum and Dad sent us to a bilingual school, so we had half the lessons in English and half in French. But I remember being hugely lost.', 68040, 0), (498881, 'We were brought up Protestant, and I went to church three times a day on a Sunday. My parents weren''t Bible-bashers, but we all have a strong belief in God and a strong faith. We had a huge garden; our house was a bit like a scene from ''The Good Life.'' I think Mam and Dad had it really hard, bringing up a big family on very little.', 70266, 0), (498882, 'My father... had sharper eyes than the rest of our people.', 4664, 0), (498883, 'I said something really stupid once. I told a friend that my mother was so beautiful, but my dad was ugly. My dad heard it and just laughed it off, but I felt guilty. It haunted me for years. I should never have said that.', 3212, 0), (498884, 'They have had such a crazy life living with me as their dad. Not crazy but different from their friends.', 71761, 0), (498885, 'Honestly, I was such a tomboy as a kid. People were taking from their mothers'' closets - I was taking from my dad''s closet. It was the ''80s, so it wasn''t terrible, but I was wearing my dad''s dress shirts over jeans from the Gap.', 2398, 0), (498886, 'I pop gum. My parents get so annoyed with me. I know my dad wishes he never taught me how to do that.', 683, 0), (498887, 'I watch political shows for a number of weeks in a row, and all I see are guys arguing with each other over issues I have no idea about. My brother, he loves war-torn places. My dad would always read the paper and tell me I should watch CNN, but I usually wind up watching ''Breaking Bad.''', 66936, 0), (498888, 'My girls are great at making fun of Dad. They''re never impressed with anything I do. I love that. I hope that never changes.', 70513, 0), (498889, 'My dad took me for an audition once, to show me, ''OK, you want to be a child actor, this is what it''s like.'' I sang a folk song about donkeys on this West End stage with this big director, and there was a queue of 200 girls all singing ''Memory.'' I was terrible. Terrible.', 71169, 0), (498890, 'My dad wanted to name me after Rainier Maria Rilke, the poet.', 30291, 0), (498891, 'The entertainment industry isn''t a line of work encouraged in the Persian culture. When I called my dad to say I wanted to quit medicine, there was about three minutes of silence. I''m not sure he knew what to do with himself!', 71508, 0), (498892, 'Watching your husband become a father is really sexy and wonderful.', 18113, 0), (498893, 'My dad works in child protection and he''s spent many, many years in that line of work.', 73012, 0), (498894, 'My dad talks about the times when we''d play backyard cricket: If I got bowled out, I''d just refuse to let go of the bat and swing it at anyone who tried to take it away from me. I like to think that''s been tempered a bit over the years.', 73012, 0), (498895, 'My dad shaped the footballing side of me, and Mum shaped me as a person. I''ve always been very close to her - we''ve only ever had one argument, and that was over something stupid when I was 13.', 47161, 0), (498896, 'I went to my dad when I was 17 and said, ''I want to be a country music star.'' Which every dad loves to hear. And he said, ''I want you to go to college.'' So we had a discussion. And I''m pretty stubborn. I''m a lot like him. And he said, ''If you go to college and graduate, I''ll pay your first six months of rent in Nashville.'' So he bribed me.', 60213, 0), (498897, 'You can''t be the dad who takes your kid out after your wife has said, ''No ice cream,'' buys the ice cream, and says, ''Don''t tell your mother.'' You teach the child to lie - and to disrespect the other parent.', 62716, 0), (498898, 'And my dad drilled it in my head, you know, ''If you want it bad enough, and you''re willing to make the sacrifices, you can do it. But first you have to believe in yourself.', 69697, 0), (498899, 'So my father was a person who never lied to me. If I had a question, he answered it. I knew a lot of things at a young age because I was intrigued.', 67879, 0), (498900, 'My dad was the town drunk. Most of the time that''s not so bad but New York City? ', 11800, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498901, 'My dad was my hero when I was a young boy. And then it''s a toss-up between Han Solo, the New Zealand All Blacks Rugby team, and Marlon Brando.', 69055, 0), (498902, 'There''s a lot of research behind the scenes that you don''t get to see, but I have an instinct that my dad nurtured from when I was born. I was very lucky then.', 15778, 0), (498903, 'When I was little, I grew up in a place called Hertfordshire, which is just near London, but out in the country, and I visited Pakistan in the summers to go and see my family on my dad''s side.', 69519, 0), (498904, 'My dad used to draw these great cartoon figures. His dream was being a cartoonist, but he never achieved it, and it kind of broke my heart. I think part of my interest in art had to do with his yearning for something he could never have.', 66653, 0), (498905, 'When we used to go to the car-wash where people would wipe the windows, my dad would go out and help them and then tip them as well, so I learned my empathy from my dad, and my mum is very empathetic too, but in a very stern way; she will always check my ego.', 69208, 0), (498906, 'The surprising thing about fatherhood was finding my inner mush. Now I want to share it with the world.', 67796, 0), (498907, 'To do a movie with someone like Tom Hanks that when you tell your dad, your dad knows who Tom Hanks is - it feels like you''re finally giving back to your parents. It''s like you''ve actually done something that they can recognize, and there''s something in me that makes them super proud.', 69720, 0), (498908, 'My dad was in the army. World War II. He got his college education from the army. After World War II he became an insurance salesman. Really, I didn''t know my dad very well. He and my mother split up after the war. I was raised by my maternal grandmother and grandfather, and by my mother.', 761, 0), (498909, 'I''m a father. It isn''t just my life any more. I don''t want my kid finding bottles in the house or seeing his father completely smashed.', 52296, 0), (498910, 'My dad always told me, ''I don''t care what you do. Just aim to be the best at it. Even if it''s the world''s best window cleaner.''', 68023, 0), (498911, 'I used to have a silk dressing gown an uncle bought in Japan and when I came downstairs in it, my dad used to call me Davinia. There was never embarrassment about that kind of thing. My sister used to dress me up a lot. She thought I was a little doll.', 17043, 0), (498912, 'I loved going to the Chiang Kai Shek Memorial in Taipei to watch all the old Chinese people doing tai chi and practicing kung fu. The monument was made of white marble, and it was beautiful. Sometimes my dad and I would practice with them.', 30158, 0), (498913, 'The whole thing for me is that I did ''Full House'' and ''America''s Funniest Home Videos,'' and I look like a dentist, and I''m a dad. Being known as a dirty comedian turned into this weird thing. It''s people''s image of me.', 70704, 0), (498914, 'My dad always jokes that we should have a reality TV show because my friends and I pull crazy stunts, like putting Saran Wrap on the toilet.', 69311, 0), (498915, 'I grew up watching my dad be a singer, so it''s something I''ve always been interested in.', 69311, 0), (498916, 'I like all the angels around because they protect me and my daughter. I mean, her Dad''s an angel.', 601, 0), (498917, 'My father never raised his hand to any one of his children, except in self-defense.', 13077, 0), (498918, 'My dad is so unique in what he does. It''s not like I''m taking a torch from him and doing his thing. I hope I''ve carried from him a little bit of a sense of irony, a little bit of a wink.', 70639, 0), (498919, 'My dad said if you become a tennis professional just make sure you get into the top hundred, because you have to make a little bit of money. You make a living so you can pay your coaching and, you know, your travels.', 67701, 0), (498920, 'All of my high school male teachers were WWII and/or Korean War veterans. They taught my brothers and me the value of service to our country and reinforced what our dad had shown us about the meaning of service.', 17647, 0), (498921, 'My dad is really just lazy. He has nothing, I feel, to offer this world.', 26862, 0), (498922, 'La Mancha is a very macho, chauvinistic society. I saw very clearly that my life had to be in Madrid, and I liberated myself from my mum and dad after high school.', 56884, 0), (498923, 'It is impossible to please all the world and one''s father.', 2843, 0), (498924, 'I''ve had some amazing people in my life. Look at my father - he came from a small fishing village of five hundred people and at six foot four with giant ears and a kind of very odd expression, thought he could be a movie star. So go figure, you know?', 67103, 0), (498925, 'Between Prince and my dad''s fusion-jazz records, I didn''t have a choice in being funky.', 56632, 0), (498926, 'I look for strong people. I don''t like people who''ll say yes to everything I might bring up. I want people who can argue and disagree and have a point of view that''s reflected in the magazine. My dad believed in the cult of personality. He brought great writers and columnists to ''The Standard.''', 1360, 0), (498927, 'My dad would call me his Cuban princess because I had really dark olive skin because I was always in the sun; but I don''t really go in the sun anymore, so that is why I am so white.', 66916, 0), (498928, 'I don''t think I have any guilt or embarrassment about any of the TV shows I watch. Maybe the fact that the shows I can watch over and over again are cartoons like ''Bob''s Burgers'' and ''American Dad'' and ''Rick & Morty.''', 69248, 0), (498929, 'Sometimes, being a single mother, I miss the freedom. I see my other friends with kids, and when they go out for a drink, it is the dad that stays in.', 70727, 0), (498930, 'I''m going to take care of the man I''m with. I grew up in a household where my mum takes care of my dad - she cooks, she does everything - and that''s the kind of girl I am.', 25639, 0), (498931, 'My dad and uncles were among the 125,000 proud black American volunteers who, throughout their entire lives, considered their decision to serve during WWII as their greatest honor.', 70728, 0), (498932, 'My dad always taught me to never be satisfied, to want more and know that what is done is done.', 68173, 0), (498933, 'To say that my dad pushed me is an understatement. I was never naturally drawn to football.', 68173, 0), (498934, 'I never saw my dad cry. My son saw me cry. My dad never told me he loved me, and consequently I told Scott I loved him every other minute. The point is, I''ll make less mistakes than my dad, my sons hopefully will make less mistakes than me, and their sons will make less mistakes than their dads.', 4803, 0), (498935, 'I''ve always liked telling stories. That probably came from my dad, who definitely had the gift of gab and who wove a kind of personal folklore about his youth - stories full of adventure and ghosts and wild antics.', 68503, 0), (498936, 'I would never have done what I''d done if I''d considered my father as somebody I wanted to please.', 74899, 0), (498937, 'People who have not done their research on me do not know that I am European, born in Copenhagen, Denmark to an Italian father from Napoli and a mother from Alabama who was singing opera and went to Europe, met my dad, fell in love, and then moved back to Rome, where I was raised, between Rome and Hamburg.', 67894, 0), (498938, 'My parents have a ridiculous work ethic; my dad just works, works, works, works, works. I think it would be hard to find a guy who''s logged more hours than that guy.', 67895, 0), (498939, 'When I was a boy, I used to pull a big cross saw with my dad. He''d use his right hand, so I''d have to use my left.', 14889, 0), (498940, 'When I was a teenager, I was an umpire for a competitive league for 8- to 9-year-olds. I was really bad at it because I didn''t know all the rules, and all these kids were better athletes than me. I made a bad call, and this dad snapped on me. Then he dumped his trash from his cooler, and I had to kick him out of the stands.', 68296, 0), (498941, 'If I took the 40 years of my dad talking to me about war and battles and taking me to battlefields and distilled it down into one question, it would probably be the idea of the necessary or unnecessary war.', 18, 0), (498942, 'What harsh judges fathers are to all young men!', 21159, 0), (498943, 'Employee fathers need to step up to the plate and put their family needs on the table.', 69527, 0), (498944, 'These things were happening in my life where I was like, ''Man, I wish my pops was here to see this.'' I never had those thoughts before fame, when my life was just a regular life. I wasn''t saying, ''I wish my dad could be around and see me working at Applebee''s.''', 69295, 0), (498945, 'My dad was an attorney. The last thing he ever thought about was clothes, and yet somehow he always looked good.', 68520, 0), (498946, 'I was going to move to New York after college and had no interest in pilot season. I''d seen what happened on TV shows because of my dad, and I didn''t want to open myself up to that. But ''Pretty Little Liars'' had a very early audition, and my agents encouraged me to go even though I didn''t think it would be my thing.', 71591, 0), (498947, 'I like wearing my dad''s sweaters because I knew that he wore them when he held me when I was a baby.', 71591, 0), (498948, 'My Dad was my biggest supporter. He never put pressure on me.', 11181, 0), (498949, 'I just went off for two months traveling around Europe on a motorcycle and pretty much turned my phone off. I did 5,000 miles with my dad. We went through Holland, Germany, Austria, Slovenia, Croatia, Bosnia, Montenegro, Italy... and then I did Spain and France by myself.', 55567, 0), (498950, 'All I want to do is be a good dad, but I''m pretty bad at it.', 13056, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (498951, 'I wanted to take up music, so my father bought me a blunt instrument. He told me to knock myself out.', 46197, 0), (498952, 'My dad used to tell me, ''Look, son, opportunity does not come knocking.'' It''s usually running down the street, and you have to chase it down, you have to tackle it, and then you have to hang on to it.', 72479, 0), (498953, 'Since I stayed in a colony where either one was an engineer or a scientist, everybody thought I would be a scientist. This was the expectation everybody had apart from my parents. Honestly, I, too, wanted to be a scientist. I think it was the way Dad would explain us scientific theories and concepts that made the subject more intriguing.', 71082, 0), (498954, 'One of my earliest memories is of my father carrying me in one arm with a picket sign in the other.', 28565, 0), (498955, 'Dad was the only adult male I ever trusted.', 76347, 0), (498956, 'Because of my father, we are that Shining City on a Hill.', 76347, 0), (498957, 'I have always thought of Walt Disney as my second father.', 73654, 0), (498958, 'Aeneas carried his aged father on his back from the ruins of Troy and so do we all, whether we like it or not, perhaps even if we have never known them.', 977, 0), (498959, 'No, I never thought about my father''s money as my money.', 66815, 0), (498960, 'My father loved people, children and pets.', 68542, 0), (498961, 'I was born and brought up in Liverpool with my clever little sister Jemma, who is 14 and wants to be a vet. My mum Jane is an administrator and my dad Peter is a taxi driver.', 70743, 0), (498962, 'My father wouldn''t get us a TV, he wouldn''t allow a TV in the house.', 12453, 0), (498963, 'I grew up in Greenwich Village. Dad was friends with John Lennon and Yoko Ono.', 71764, 0), (498964, 'I''m glad to have shown myself able to do other things rather than people thinking, ''Oh, he''ll just do the same as his dad.'' Dad was a brilliant actor, but it just so happened he was five foot five and a half, fat and bald.', 66939, 0), (498965, 'I lost my dad way too early and it was agonisingly awful. I missed him so much and I hated knowing that I could never again pick up the phone to tell him about my day.', 70309, 0), (498966, 'I grew up not liking my father very much. I never saw him cry. But he must have. Everybody cries.', 22803, 0), (498967, 'I wanted my dad to be proud of me, and I fell into acting because there wasn''t anything else I could do, and in it I found a discipline that I wanted to keep coming back to, that I love and I learn about every day.', 69286, 0), (498968, 'I was always the new kid in school, I''m the kid from a broken family, I''m the kid who had no dad showing up at the father-son stuff, I''m the kid that was using food stamps at the grocery store.', 8226, 0), (498969, 'My father taught me how to substitute realities.', 47511, 0), (498970, 'When I was younger it was - you know, my dad dressed up in drag on ''Bosom Buddies.'' And that was what I was having to deal with at the time. And then around the time that I was into college was when he became statue-worthy I guess you could say.', 76348, 0), (498971, 'My dad is a much more flamboyant character than I am. I think that''s why I couldn''t see myself going into straight acting. I always just felt daft.', 75212, 0), (498972, 'The script for ''In Good Company'' was the first one I ever showed my dad.', 68417, 0), (498973, 'Creativity runs across many categories in life, from the arts-and-crafts project a mum or dad does with their kids, to the bestselling author''s manuscript, to the designs of the hairdresser, to the creations of the computer programming genius.', 66932, 0), (498974, 'I didn''t always want to be a dad.', 71701, 0), (498975, 'I had to learn how to chop wood actually - I don''t think my dad would have let me go chop wood in the backyard growing up.', 47254, 0), (498976, 'Can I play a southern character? You betcha. Can I do the voice of Tourist Dad and Carnival Barker? Ya betcha. Can I do Fix-It Felix? Ya betcha. But I don''t want to just play southern characters, so I hide it; I bury it. I tamp it down like a secret. Like a dirty little secret.', 76349, 0), (498977, 'I''m being a dad and a good husband.', 68565, 0), (498978, 'I''m a fun father, but not a good father. The hard decisions always went to my wife.', 68308, 0), (498979, 'When it came to the stylish and graceful art of ballroom dancing, my dad was a king of the clubs, a prowling tiger and a wonderfully natural mover.', 76350, 0), (498980, 'My dad is a huge rock and roll lead guitar fan. I didn''t even really know that until recently. Everything has to have a guitar solo in it.', 22833, 0), (498981, 'My dad taught me true words you have to use in every relationship. Yes, baby.', 71332, 0), (498982, 'My father was the most rational and the most dispassionate of men.', 70454, 0), (498983, 'I''m sure there was some part of his soul was intrinsically happy, but he probably had to go through some permutations to really get that to blossom. I''m sure Dad had his challenges, but I think that joy was there from the beginning and he had to find a way to make his life support that and express that.', 68368, 0), (498984, 'I remember going on carriage rides with Dad when we''d visit. I think quiet L.A. suited him better, but he loved to see shows here, he loved to visit his friends in the Hamptons.', 68368, 0), (498985, 'My brothers bullied me, so I cried a lot as a kid. It was the only defense I had. Telling them to stop wouldn''t work. The crying would bring my dad. Dad was my cavalry.', 73206, 0), (498986, 'But you know, my dad called me the laziest white kid he ever met. When I screamed back at him that he was putting down a race of people to call me lazy, his answer was that''s not what he was doing, and that I was also the dumbest white kid he ever met.', 68569, 0), (498987, 'I''m Bam Margera. And I feel like kicking my dad''s butt all day today.', 76351, 0), (498988, 'When you grow up on a dairy farm, cows don''t take a day off. So you work every day and my dad always said, ''No one can outwork you.''', 33654, 0), (498989, 'I haven''t really decided to be an actor yet! I started doing plays when I was about 15 or 16. I only did it because my dad saw a bunch of pretty girls in a restaurant and he asked them where they came from and they said drama group. He said, ''Son, that is where you need to go.''', 68798, 0), (498990, 'And in that time, I lost my dad and had kids of my own. It was like, OK, I get it now. I know what fatherhood is all about. And you look at your parents differently.', 12009, 0), (498991, 'I look at my little girl and I wonder what she''s going to be and what she''s going to do and what is it that leads girls certain directions in life. I think a lot of that goes back to what kind of father they had, and so it makes me want to be the best dad I can possibly be.', 73147, 0), (498992, 'As a little girl I used to daydream about my real father coming on a white horse to rescue me.', 73080, 0), (498993, 'I could share an hour of warm camaraderie with Dad, then once I''d walked out the door, get the uncanny feeling I''d disappeared into the wings of his mind''s stage, like a character no longer necessary to the ongoing story line.', 72322, 0), (498994, 'Roman history was kind of unavoidable where I was growing up. It was everywhere - all the place names and ruins and forts. My dad''s a history buff, and I spent a lot of time on Hadrian''s Wall. I became fascinated by the idea of what was so terrifying up there that the Romans built a 60-mile long, 30ft high stone wall to keep it out?', 76352, 0), (498995, 'I was the third son, and the family tradition was my dad always favored the oldest child.', 76353, 0), (498996, 'Thirteen, 13 children, and I love - I love them all. And I think I''ve been a good father to all of them.', 74095, 0), (498997, 'When I stopped playing hockey and started acting, the last person I was going to ask for help was my dad. He''s the king of being like, ''I don''t know. It''s good work if you can get it. Good luck.''', 76354, 0), (498998, 'According to my parents, I just started drumming when I was two. I traveled with them from five to seven on the road, playing percussion. Between 8 and 12, my dad sort of prepared me by teaching me every aspect of road life.', 71673, 0), (498999, 'You''ve got to take the road you need to take, and only you can make that calculation. Not your dad, not your friend. You have to take it if you feel it instinctively.', 55930, 0), (499000, 'A father''s disappointment can be a very powerful tool.', 74741, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (499001, 'As a kid growing up, I wanted the Allen Iverson shoes that came out, the Questions. My dad got them for me, so I was excited about that.', 70498, 0), (499002, 'I was born in a hurricane in Pensacola, Florida... my dad was in the military, so we moved all over the place. But I consider myself a southerner from Louisiana. I''ve lived in Texas for most of my adult life.', 8177, 0), (499003, 'I didn''t want to play a lawyer. I didn''t want to play a doctor. I didn''t want to play a single dad. I wanted to do something I felt I could learn from, something that would be a challenge and something that would not dry up.', 27755, 0), (499004, 'My dad is a really honest, hardworking, straight guy.', 73238, 0), (499005, 'Out of all my friends, I believe I''m the only kid whose dad made us work to cut rebars; we laid bricks in construction sites and did other real work every summer for minimum wage. Our dad said that it''s important in the future that when we tell people to dig a hole, that you personally know how long it will take to dig that hole.', 74306, 0), (499006, 'I love my dad, although I''m definitely critical of him sometimes, like when his pants are too tight. But I love him so much and I try to be really supportive of him.', 69252, 0), (499007, 'I can''t remember a major league game where I could make eye contact with my dad. I kept wondering if he was going to yell at me for hanging a pitch or something.', 73350, 0), (499008, 'My dad put up a great hoop in our front yard in our driveway. I was in Oregon, so I had to be out there in the rain. We didn''t always have a gym to go to.', 76355, 0), (499009, 'I was lucky. A lot of people have that. People that don''t tell you what you want to hear, but what''s best for you. I was blessed with great friends. I was always blessed that way. My dad always kept good people around me. I just got lucky. Because of the spotlight you''re in, people are scared to tell you otherwise.', 76355, 0), (499010, 'From my first dunk at 14 years old to my second NCAA Championship at the University of Tennessee, my intense training with my dad was always to credit.', 68132, 0), (499011, 'Father told me that if I ever met a lady in a dress like yours, I must look her straight in the eyes.', 73033, 0), (499012, 'I suppose not everyone has a dad who wrote a book saying he didn''t believe in the Parliamentary road to socialism.', 71531, 0), (499013, 'I want to know everything there is to know about Lewis and Clark. And I want to do the Sunday crossword in less than an hour. I want to be the best dad in the world. I want to play Richard II, and I want to win another Tony award.', 76356, 0), (499014, 'And I remember leaving my place in L.A. and - my father is a big fight fan - and I said, ''Dad, I got a couple of days off and I''m getting ready to go to Houston to sign to fight Muhammad Ali.', 59443, 0), (499015, 'I remember opening my dad''s closet and there were, like, 40 suits, every color of the rainbow, plaid and winter and summer. He had two jewelry boxes full of watches and lighters and cuff links. And just... he was that guy. He was probably unfulfilled in his life in many ways.', 67944, 0), (499016, 'I don''t think there''s any real motivation for somebody to be a truck driver. Mine was simple; dad was a truck driver, I wanted to own one.', 66561, 0), (499017, 'When I was a kid, I used to imagine animals running under my bed. I told my dad, and he solved the problem quickly. He cut the legs off the bed.', 73728, 0), (499018, 'I''m a dad, and I can tell you it''s the most beautiful thing in the world.', 76357, 0), (499019, 'Being a dad is like - there''s nothing more important. So the exploration of that in stories, with parents and fathers and brothers, siblings, I just think that you''re always in the terrain of love, whether it''s absence of love or the giving of love or the desire for love.', 76358, 0), (499020, 'I was actually born in L.A. My sisters and I were playing in a parking lot, and my dad was like, ''Nah, nah, nah. Let''s go give ''em some grass.''', 69979, 0), (499021, 'My father was something of a rainbow-chaser.', 76359, 0), (499022, 'I promised my daughter I''d name my first restaurant after her, but now the other kids are like, ''Dad, what about us?'' I''m gonna have to open four restaurants!', 43830, 0), (499023, 'My father was always telling himself no one was perfect, not even my mother.', 76360, 0), (499024, 'A mustache really defines your face. My dad had a mustache when I was growing up, and I can still remember when he shaved it, he looked like a completely different person.', 74968, 0), (499025, 'On the death of his brothers, my dad lied about his age and joined the army in 1918. He was in the trenches long enough to be gassed and contract the early stages of tuberculosis from which he would eventually die just before my birth.', 75153, 0), (499026, 'I know who my dad is, I''ve met him a few times, but I don''t even call him dad. I know it sounds horrible, but I don''t even see him as part of my family, to be honest. If you want the truth, it doesn''t bother me because I don''t know any different. I just know that me and my mum, that was my family.', 76361, 0), (499027, 'My father was the guy on the block who said hi to everyone.', 72735, 0), (499028, 'My dad was such a bigot. He was a horrible, self-centred person. He was really racist and he''d talk about the Jews and blacks and Catholics even.', 76362, 0), (499029, 'When I was 10, I had a paper route. One year, I delivered my papers through a hurricane. My mother was against the idea, but my dad, who was a sergeant in the Marine Corps, overruled her. I was determined to deliver my papers.', 74275, 0), (499030, 'Just growing up, my dad always told me the most important point of the game is the extra point. A lot of people take that play off. It''s an opportunity to make something happen, and I''m going to make the most of it.', 73010, 0), (499031, 'When you break it all down, my punk rock is my dad''s blues. It''s music from the underground, and it''s real, and it''s written for the downtrodden in uncertain times.', 71698, 0), (499032, 'The best money advice ever given me was from my father. When I was a little girl, he told me, ''Don''t spend anything unless you have to.''', 62525, 0), (499033, 'My dad always said there''s four phases in an actor/director''s life. There''s ''Mario Who?'' There''s ''Get me Mario!'' ''Get me a young Mario,'' and ''Mario Who?''', 67266, 0), (499034, 'When my dad first started out in the police force, wearing the uniform was a sense of pride, and it was respected in the community for what the police force was all about. Unfortunately today, the uniform is a target.', 71861, 0), (499035, 'One of my earliest memories is my father telling me to behave because I''m about to meet and work with the greatest actor of all time. Then this old guy comes out and I was like, ''Pfff, he doesn''t look anything like Luke Skywalker, I don''t know what my dad is trying to tell me here.''', 76363, 0), (499036, 'My dad has worked so hard his whole life. He doesn''t deserve to see his daughters going out embarrassing themselves and flashing their knickers. I want to make my parents proud.', 72032, 0), (499037, 'I come from an artistic family. My dad''s an actor, my mother''s an actress, my sister''s an actress. So I kind of grew up in that kind of environment. Oddly enough, I never really knew about my parents'' work. I''ve seen small clips of it, but we never actually spoke about the business.', 74531, 0), (499038, 'I think once I fail enough as a dad, I''ll be looking for help wherever I can get it. I just need enough time to screw things up and then I''ll start looking to TV dads for advice.', 69808, 0), (499039, 'I grew up with lacrosse in my life because my dad played lacrosse all throughout college, so I grew up with the gear in my house - like the sticks, the helmet.', 71021, 0), (499040, 'I know when I''m not dancing, and I go home, I usually work with my dad, who''s an electrician. So I do stuff like that. I used to be a landscape gardener. I loved that job. But I''d like to be involved with entertainment. Singing or something, I guess.', 67275, 0), (499041, 'My father invented a cure for which there was no disease and unfortunately my mother caught it and died of it.', 2249, 0), (499042, 'That is the thankless position of the father in the family - the provider for all, and the enemy of all.', 8978, 0), (499043, 'Father or stepfather - those are just titles to me. They don''t mean anything.', 72222, 0), (499044, 'Fathers in today''s modern families can be so many things.', 72222, 0), (499045, 'My dad was a bass player in a Latino band when I was growing up. So we always had musical instruments in our basement.', 76364, 0), (499046, 'I grew up on film sets and I had a ball. It wouldn''t have had nearly as much fun if my dad had been working behind a desk somewhere. I remember being on the set of ''The Godfather: Part III,'' and all the kids were running around and doing crazy things, and Francis Ford Coppola just embraced that.', 76365, 0), (499047, 'I wanted to emulate my parents - Mum captained India in basketball, and Dad won a bronze in hockey in 1972 Olympics. My focus has always been to achieve excellence whether in the field of tennis, in the corporate field, in the art of acting or in motivating youngsters.', 76366, 0), (499048, 'Being a father to my family and a husband is to me much more important than what I did in the business.', 76367, 0), (499049, 'My dad always said, ''Don''t worry what people think, because you can''t change it.''', 76368, 0), (499050, 'I''m lucky to have my dad in my life. He''s very brilliant, I think he''s really a smart man, and he''s a kind guy.', 74438, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (499051, 'I''m a dad and a husband, and so the things that I love to do are all geared around my family.', 76369, 0), (499052, 'As soon as I was tall enough, my dad used to let me drive him 60 miles or 70 miles to work. That was pretty fun. My dad was really old. At the time, he was 82 years old. He said, ''Can you drive?'' and I said ''Yes.'' I guess I didn''t find it to be that crazy.', 76370, 0), (499053, 'You see people you identify with, and you take pieces of people you like and shape who you are. Like, I sound just like my dad. But that''s literally my vocal chords. I can''t sound like anything else... I sound like him, but I act like myself.', 72735, 0), (499054, 'I have this complex. I don''t like too much exposure. I don''t know why it is. Maybe it''s bred in me, because my dad always told me to be humble and don''t think you''re too good.', 76371, 0), (499055, 'I actually wanted to be a police officer like my dad for the longest time, up until my sophomore year in high school when I started doing plays. I did plays when I was little, but in high school, I started getting into acting.', 76372, 0), (499056, 'Whenever we went on a trip, picnic, or business trip, I was always with my dad, and I would just always be in contact with cosmonauts, and I thought it would be always normal to be with them.', 76373, 0), (499057, 'I knew Sinatra for 38 years. He was like my father. Frank Sinatra was my ''dad.'' He treated me like his son. He gave me the best advice about singing, about this and that... He was a very sensitive man, very astute, one of the sharpest men that I ever met in my life.', 67313, 0), (499058, 'My father was never anti-anything in our house.', 69000, 0), (499059, 'It is much easier to become a father than to be one.', 5155, 0), (499060, 'My dad''s a Republican. My dad''s my mentor. When I was 18 or whatever it was and I decided to register to vote. My dad''s Republican, so that''s what I decided to register as.', 76374, 0), (499061, 'My father was an Episcopalian minister, and I''ve always been comforted by the power of prayer.', 75665, 0), (499062, 'My dad keeps referring to me playing the piano when he''s trying to teach me something in archery.', 59575, 0), (499063, 'Rich men''s sons are seldom rich men''s fathers.', 63081, 0), (499064, 'My dad actually taught me how to do the catwalk because he used to do modeling. He taught me how to do that little swivel at the end.', 76375, 0), (499065, 'When a father, absent during the day, returns home at six, his children receive only his temperament, not his teaching.', 8729, 0), (499066, 'As my dad said, you have an obligation to leave the world better than how you found it. And he also reminded us to be givers in this life, and not takers.', 75120, 0), (499067, 'No man is responsible for his father. That was entirely his mother''s affair.', 76376, 0), (499068, 'It is not weird for a dad to be doing the dishes, the laundry, and taking the kids to school, and read them stories for bed.', 69185, 0), (499069, 'I always thought that family was the most important thing in life, and no matter what I do, whether being a chef or an actor or a dancer, being a dad is what I do best.', 70553, 0), (499070, 'You cannot escape the responsibility of tomorrow by evading it today.', 1012, 0), (499071, 'Keep looking up! I learn from the past, dream about the future and look up. There''s nothing like a beautiful sunset to end a healthy day.', 73156, 0), (499072, 'I''m looking forward to the future, and feeling grateful for the past.', 6052, 0), (499073, 'The secret of your future is hidden in your daily routine.', 36716, 0), (499074, 'Memories are the key not to the past, but to the future.', 533, 0), (499075, 'Planning is bringing the future into the present so that you can do something about it now.', 12843, 0), (499076, 'You never know what the future holds, so I am just enjoying being happy, healthy, and having my wonderful husband by my side.', 69114, 0), (499077, 'If we open a quarrel between past and present, we shall find that we have lost the future.', 3621, 0), (499078, 'The future belongs to those who prepare for it today.', 1730, 0), (499079, 'If you think in terms of a year, plant a seed; if in terms of ten years, plant trees; if in terms of 100 years, teach the people.', 819, 0), (499080, 'The future is green energy, sustainability, renewable energy.', 12194, 0), (499081, 'In this bright future you can''t forget your past.', 7, 0), (499082, 'What we need to do is always lean into the future when the world changes around you and when it changes against you - what used to be a tail wind is now a head wind - you have to lean into that and figure out what to do because complaining isn''t a strategy. ', 22320, 0), (499083, 'A person often meets his destiny on the road he took to avoid it.', 2843, 0), (499084, 'People sacrifice the present for the future. But life is available only in the present. That is why we should walk in such a way that every step can bring us to the here and the now.', 394, 0), (499085, 'We all have a responsibility to protect endangered species, both for their sake and for the sake of our own future generations.', 69071, 0), (499086, 'It is up to us to live up to the legacy that was left for us, and to leave a legacy that is worthy of our children and of future generations.', 70455, 0), (499087, 'When I look into the future, it''s so bright it burns my eyes.', 588, 0), (499088, 'Study the past, if you would divine the future.', 819, 0), (499089, 'There is always one moment in childhood when the door opens and lets the future in.', 429, 0), (499090, 'If we intend to provide a better life, and a better world, for future generations, we can''t ignore the quality of the environment we leave them.', 42443, 0), (499091, 'Prejudice is a burden that confuses the past, threatens the future and renders the present inaccessible.', 74, 0), (499092, 'The human brain had a vast memory storage. It made us curious and very creative. Those were the characteristics that gave us an advantage - curiosity, creativity and memory. And that brain did something very special. It invented an idea called ''the future.''', 13824, 0), (499093, 'If recycling is the future, then we must focus our efforts on mitigating negative impacts to our community while protecting our environment.', 70446, 0), (499094, 'The challenge of the unknown future is so much more exciting than the stories of the accomplished past.', 19485, 0), (499095, 'If my future were determined just by my performance on a standardized test, I wouldn''t be here. I guarantee you that.', 1997, 0), (499096, 'Innovation is the calling card of the future.', 72459, 0), (499097, 'My parents taught me to never give up and to always believe that my future could be whatever I dreamt it to be.', 66800, 0), (499098, 'The future of advertising is the Internet.', 1133, 0), (499099, 'Control your own destiny or someone else will.', 10103, 0), (499100, 'No valid plans for the future can be made by those who have no capacity for living now.', 45466, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (499101, 'Only you can control your future.', 3, 0), (499102, 'Real generosity toward the future lies in giving all to the present.', 532, 0), (499103, 'Elegance is not the prerogative of those who have just escaped from adolescence, but of those who have already taken possession of their future.', 111, 0), (499104, 'Sustainability, ensuring the future of life on Earth, is an infinite game, the endless expression of generosity on behalf of all.', 21310, 0), (499105, 'Without ethics, man has no future. This is to say, mankind without them cannot be itself. Ethics determine choices and actions and suggest difficult priorities.', 1307, 0), (499106, 'The past, like the future, is indefinite and exists only as a spectrum of possibilities.', 1222, 0), (499107, 'I am not interested in the past, except as the road to the future.', 55176, 0), (499108, 'Every man gotta right to decide his own destiny.', 7, 0), (499109, 'It is our job, as members of parliament, to legislate with an eye to the long term future, to look over the horizon beyond the next election and ensure that as far as we can what we do today will make Australia a better place, a safer place, for future generations to live in.', 72454, 0), (499110, 'Social media... it''s the future for the new generation.', 70063, 0), (499111, 'Look back over the past, with its changing empires that rose and fell, and you can foresee the future, too.', 267, 0), (499112, 'Time passed solely in the pursuit of pleasure leaves no solid enjoyment for the future; but from the hours you spend in reading and studying useful books, you will gather a golden harvest in future years.', 3921, 0), (499113, 'Because of lack of moral principle, human life becomes worthless. Moral principle, truthfulness, is a key factor. If we lose that, then there is no future.', 5025, 0), (499114, 'I am tomorrow, or some future day, what I establish today. I am today what I established yesterday or some previous day.', 265, 0), (499115, 'Discontent, blaming, complaining, self-pity cannot serve as a foundation for a good future, no matter how much effort you make.', 378, 0), (499116, 'Do your duty and a little more and the future will take care of itself.', 4963, 0), (499117, 'We drive into the future using only our rearview mirror.', 2728, 0), (499118, 'Let us make future generations remember us as proud ancestors just as, today, we remember our forefathers.', 76377, 0), (499119, 'School is practice for the future, and practice makes perfect. But nobody''s perfect, so why practice?', 52296, 0), (499120, 'Prediction is very difficult, especially if it''s about the future.', 2826, 0), (499121, 'Diversification and globalization are the keys to the future.', 76378, 0), (499122, 'My purpose... to go on with my heart and soul, devoting all my energies to Girl Scouts, and heart and hand with them, we will make our lives and the lives of the future girls happy, healthy and holy.', 69097, 0), (499123, 'Leaders establish the vision for the future and set the strategy for getting there.', 68859, 0), (499124, 'Future generations are not going to ask us what political party were you in. They are going to ask what did you do about it, when you knew the glaciers were melting.', 10201, 0), (499125, 'When the past no longer illuminates the future, the spirit walks in darkness.', 4021, 0), (499126, 'The only difference between the saint and the sinner is that every saint has a past, and every sinner has a future.', 40, 0), (499127, 'I don''t try to describe the future. I try to prevent it.', 567, 0), (499128, 'It is always wise to look ahead, but difficult to look further than you can see.', 3621, 0), (499129, 'The future influences the present just as much as the past.', 11, 0), (499130, 'Destiny has two ways of crushing us - by refusing our wishes and by fulfilling them.', 4754, 0), (499131, 'The influence of teachers extends beyond the classroom, well into the future. It is they who shape and enrich the minds of the young, who touch their hearts and souls. It is they who shape a nation''s future.', 16120, 0), (499132, 'Parents are like shuttles on a loom. They join the threads of the past with threads of the future and leave their own bright patterns as they go.', 167, 0), (499133, 'If you see the magic in a fairy tale, you can face the future.', 5214, 0), (499134, 'I''m not good at future planning. I don''t plan at all. I don''t know what I''m doing tomorrow. I don''t have a day planner and I don''t have a diary. I completely live in the now, not in the past, not in the future.', 53389, 0), (499135, 'The future is no more uncertain than the present.', 1127, 0), (499136, 'The past is a ghost, the future a dream, and all we ever have is now.', 2059, 0), (499137, 'The future battle on the ground will be preceded by battle in the air. This will determine which of the contestants has to suffer operational and tactical disadvantages and be forced throughout the battle into adoption compromise solutions.', 16072, 0), (499138, 'For every minute, the future is becoming the past.', 35520, 0), (499139, 'Trying to predict the future is like trying to drive down a country road at night with no lights while looking out the back window.', 37852, 0), (499140, 'The only thing we know about the future is that it will be different.', 37852, 0), (499141, 'The present was an egg laid by the past that had the future inside its shell.', 751, 0), (499142, 'America is false to the past, false to the present, and solemnly binds herself to be false to the future.', 7432, 0), (499143, 'You have to focus on the future and know that you can succeed in life, and you have to keep working hard.', 67080, 0), (499144, 'They might in the future more than ever before engage in hunting beavers.', 75893, 0), (499145, 'To that movement, consecrated by religious principle, sustained by an awful sense of justice, and cheered by the brightest hopes of future good, all our powers, talents, and attainments are devoted.', 75894, 0), (499146, 'Map out your future - but do it in pencil. The road ahead is as long as you make it. Make it worth the trip.', 2385, 0), (499147, 'If humanity doesn''t land on Mars in my lifetime, I would be very disappointed.', 10864, 0), (499148, 'The future is built on brains, not prom court, as most people can tell you after attending their high school reunion. But you''d never know it by talking to kids or listening to the messages they get from the culture and even from their schools.', 1552, 0), (499149, 'I got a bright future ahead of me.', 957, 0), (499150, 'Children have neither a past nor a future. Thus they enjoy the present, which seldom happens to us.', 5879, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (499151, 'Adolescence represents an inner emotional upheaval, a struggle between the eternal human wish to cling to the past and the equally powerful wish to get on with the future.', 71567, 0), (499152, 'A dream collage is pictures of your goals. It is like your future photo album.', 3499, 0), (499153, 'Our Heavenly Father knows us and our circumstances and even what faces us in the future. His Beloved Son, Jesus Christ, our Savior, has suffered and paid for our sins and those of all the people we will ever meet. He has perfect understanding of the feelings, the suffering, the trials, and the needs of every individual.', 9158, 0), (499154, 'Leaders don''t look backwards to condemn what has already been done they look forward to create a better future. ', 35063, 0), (499155, 'All political thinking for years past has been vitiated in the same way. People can foresee the future only when it coincides with their own wishes, and the most grossly obvious facts can be ignored when they are unwelcome.', 521, 0), (499156, 'Living in the moment, thinking about the future, and staying connected to the past: That''s what makes me feel whole.', 38121, 0), (499157, 'People don''t realize that now is all there ever is there is no past or future except as memory or anticipation in your mind. ', 378, 0), (499158, 'I really believe in the idea of the future.', 68727, 0), (499159, 'The empires of the future are the empires of the mind.', 3621, 0), (499160, 'Right now people are interested in genetic engineering to help the human race. That''s a noble cause, and that''s where we should be heading. But once we get past that - once we understand what genetic diseases we can deal with - when we start thinking about the future, there''s an opportunity to create some new life-forms.', 48964, 0), (499161, 'Humans are the only creatures with the ability to dive deep in the sea, fly high in the sky, send instant messages around the globe, reflect on the past, assess the present and imagine the future.', 67053, 0), (499162, 'I know of no way of judging the future but by the past.', 3269, 0), (499163, 'I look to the future because that''s where I''m going to spend the rest of my life.', 1643, 0), (499164, 'I''m living my future as long as you''re living in the present and realize how beautiful life is.', 20109, 0), (499165, 'Whenever in future wars the battle is fought, armored troops will play the decisive role.', 76379, 0), (499166, 'At some future period, not very distant as measured by centuries, the civilized races of man will almost certainly exterminate, and replace the savage races throughout the world.', 1024, 0), (499167, 'I take all of my life lessons, which some people might call ''mistakes,'' and apply them to my future so that I keep growing.', 76380, 0), (499168, 'Promises are the uniquely human way of ordering the future, making it predictable and reliable to the extent that this is humanly possible.', 2694, 0), (499169, 'Let others lead small lives, but not you. Let others argue over small things, but not you. Let others cry over small hurts, but not you. Let others leave their future in someone else''s hands, but not you.', 1295, 0), (499170, 'The factory of the future will have only two employees, a man and a dog. The man will be there to feed the dog. The dog will be there to keep the man from touching the equipment.', 19589, 0), (499171, 'The hacker community may be small, but it possesses the skills that are driving the global economies of the future.', 67067, 0), (499172, 'The real enemies of our life are the ''oughts'' and the ''ifs.'' They pull us backward into the unalterable past and forward into the unpredictable future. But real life takes place in the here and now.', 19097, 0), (499173, 'I don''t carry the burden of the past or the madness of the future. I live in the present.', 40212, 0), (499174, 'The potential for synthetic biology and biotechnology is vast we all have an opportunity to create the future together. ', 13777, 0), (499175, 'We have to do with the past only as we can make it useful to the present and the future.', 7432, 0), (499176, 'I am not like a pebble on the beach - a grain of sand on the seashore or just one of millions of human beings past, present and future. No, I am a unique human being loved by God as if I were an only child - the only fruit of his creative powers.', 9130, 0), (499177, 'The earth we abuse and the living things we kill will, in the end, take their revenge; for in exploiting their presence we are diminishing our future.', 16394, 0), (499178, 'There is an opportunity for us to renew ourselves. There''s an opportunity for us to leave the past behind and present something different for the future.', 67898, 0), (499179, 'Even a brief interaction can change the way people think about themselves, their leaders, and the future. Each of those many connections you make has the potential to become a high point or a low point in someone''s day.', 69529, 0), (499180, 'Listen, you know this: If there''s not a rebellious youth culture, there''s no culture at all. It''s absolutely essential. It is the future. This is what we''re supposed to do as a species, is advance ideas.', 14227, 0), (499181, 'As a leader, I am tough on myself and I raise the standard for everybody; however, I am very caring because I want people to excel at what they are doing so that they can aspire to be me in the future.', 34991, 0), (499182, 'The distinction between the past, present and future is only a stubbornly persistent illusion.', 104, 0), (499183, 'Let us put our minds together and see what life we can make for our children.', 48992, 0), (499184, 'If we can''t begin to agree on fundamentals, such as the elimination of the most abusive forms of child labor, then we really are not ready to march forward into the future.', 70476, 0), (499185, 'To make any future that we dreamt up real requires creative scientists, engineers, and technologists to make it happen. If people are not within your midst who dream about tomorrow - with the capacity to bring tomorrow into the present - then the country might as well just recede back into the cave because that''s where we''re headed.', 404, 0), (499186, 'Let them look to the past, but let them also look to the future; let them look to the land of their ancestors, but let them look also to the land of their children.', 62755, 0), (499187, 'We already have the statistics for the future: the growth percentages of pollution, overpopulation, desertification. The future is already in place.', 5995, 0), (499188, 'Every thought we think is creating our future.', 5296, 0), (499189, 'Accordingly, globalization is not only something that will concern and threaten us in the future, but something that is taking place in the present and to which we must first open our eyes.', 66823, 0), (499190, 'I have learned to live each day as it comes, and not to borrow trouble by dreading tomorrow. It is the dark menace of the future that makes cowards of us.', 3638, 0), (499191, 'Therefore I am sure that this, my Coronation, is not the symbol of a power and a splendor that are gone but a declaration of our hopes for the future, and for the years I may, by God''s Grace and Mercy, be given to reign and serve you as your Queen.', 65677, 0), (499192, 'The first principle of contract negotiations is don''t remind them of what you did in the past - tell them what you''re going to do in the future.', 65254, 0), (499193, 'Broadcasting is definitely in my cards for the future, and I''m determined to work hard at it - to perfect it and create my style and niche.', 68124, 0), (499194, 'I''m always looking to the future and what will next be on the horizon.', 67848, 0), (499195, 'For all my years in public life, I have believed that America must sail toward the shores of liberty and justice for all. There is no end to that journey, only the next great voyage. We know the future will outlast all of us, but I believe that all of us will live on in the future we make.', 73043, 0), (499196, 'The future ain''t what it used to be.', 1896, 0), (499197, 'The past, the present and the future are really one: they are today.', 3252, 0), (499198, 'The euro is our common fate, and Europe is our common future.', 67556, 0), (499199, 'At every crossroads on the path that leads to the future, tradition has placed 10,000 men to guard the past.', 2006, 0), (499200, 'My wish for the new millennium is for all children... to grow up wiser, and stronger and more prosperous for the future than ever before.', 66567, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (499201, 'Your customers can tell you the things that are broken and how they want to be made happy. Listen to them. Make them happy. But don''t rely on them to create the future road map for your product or service. That''s your job.', 35063, 0), (499202, 'I can''t speak for the future. I have no crystal ball.', 1813, 0), (499203, 'Enjoy present pleasures in such a way as not to injure future ones.', 1379, 0), (499204, 'We deal here with the right of all of our children, whatever their race, to an equal start in life and to an equal opportunity to reach their full potential as citizens. Those children who have been denied that right in the past deserve better than to see fences thrown up to deny them that right in the future.', 14586, 0), (499205, 'My own view is that being a vegetarian or vegan is not an end in itself, but a means towards reducing both human and animal suffering and leaving a habitable planet to future generations.', 2537, 0), (499206, 'For 50 years, nuclear power stations have produced three products which only a lunatic could want: bomb-explosive plutonium, lethal radioactive waste and electricity so dear it has to be heavily subsidised. They leave to future generations the task, and most of the cost, of making safe sites that have been polluted half-way to eternity.', 68800, 0), (499207, 'Cease to inquire what the future has in store, and take as a gift whatever the day brings forth.', 2542, 0), (499208, 'Hold fast to the Bible. To the influence of this Book we are indebted for all the progress made in true civilization and to this we must look as our guide in the future.', 9689, 0), (499209, 'There''s no place that communicates as much - and as quickly - as Times Square does. I see the roiling energy and its forceful race into the future. Of course, after 15 minutes, I want to get as far away from there as possible.', 76381, 0), (499210, 'Partition is bad. But whatever is past is past. 