iritual experiences gave my future life its form and content.', 49246, 0), (499378, 'Unification is not our present goal. That is a future program.', 75374, 0), (499379, 'When you realize the value of all life, you dwell less on what is past and concentrate more on the preservation of the future.', 21980, 0), (499380, 'Reactionary: a man walking backwards with his face to the future.', 17538, 0), (499381, 'The future is the worst thing about the present.', 647, 0), (499382, 'I would vote against raising the national debt ceiling. Again, this is about mortgaging the future of unborn generations of Americans. It''s a form of taxation without representation. I don''t think we can do that.', 75391, 0), (499383, 'If a product''s future is unlikely to be remarkable - if you can''t imagine a future in which people are once again fascinated by your product - it''s time to realize that the game has changed. Instead of investing in a dying product, take profits and reinvest them in building something new.', 2113, 0), (499384, 'A nation that does not stand for its children does not stand for anything and will not stand tall in the future.', 7224, 0), (499385, 'Our future is our sense of common destiny.', 67273, 0), (499386, 'Web 2.0 ideas have a chirpy, cheerful rhetoric to them, but I think they consistently express a profound pessimism about humans, human nature and the human future.', 2743, 0), (499387, 'Western Christians have imagined that, at the end of the day, God is going to throw the present space-time universe into a trashcan and we''ll be sitting on clouds playing harps. The ultimate future that we''re promised is much more interesting than that. It''s new heavens and a new Earth with new bodies to live in.', 4251, 0), (499388, 'Once we agree on the future, the present will be much easier. A captain who does not know where he wants to sail, there is no wind on Earth that will bring him there. We have first to decide where we want to go, where we want to sail.', 763