y situation, no matter what the future may hold.', 10856, 0), (499484, 'We know from chaos theory that even if you had a perfect model of the world, you''d need infinite precision in order to predict future events. With sociopolitical or economic phenomena, we don''t have anything like that.', 2505, 0), (499485, 'I''m not much for sitting around and thinking about the past or talking about the past. What does that accomplish? If I can give young people something to think about, like the future, that''s a better use of my time.', 24450, 0), (499486, 'To me, living in the present means being aware of your conscious choice to focus on the past, present or future - it is not necessarily having to focus on the present.', 3499, 0), (499487, 'I have no plans, and no plans to plan.', 8855, 0), (499488, 'I really don''t spend time thinking about the past. I think about the future. I''m not stopping.', 67678, 0), (499489, 'I just don''t want to live like I used to. And at some point, I''m going to put a gag order on myself in terms of talking about the past. I''ve got to slam the door and deal with the present and the future.', 23240, 0), (499490, 'Through the Fellows Program, Acumen Fund prepares future global leaders with the tools necessary to drive significant social change.', 19566, 0), (499491, 'When you get just a complete sense of blackness or void ahead of you, that somehow the future looks an impossible place to be, and the direction you are going seems to have no purpose, there is this word despair which is a very awful thing to feel.', 1031, 0), (499492, 'I can look at the future with anticipation. And it''s comforting to know that someday, as Christians, we''ll be able to look back and have a little more clarity on why certain things in life happened.', 64661, 0), (499493, 'The task of a university is the creation of the future, so far as rational thought and civilized modes of appreciation can affect the issue.', 2606, 0), (499494, 'There are times when even the